title: vegetable medley(serves 35)
directions: Heat oil and add vegetables that have been sliced. Cook 5 minutes, covered.
Stir in wine; simmer 10 minutes, uncovered. Add butter and stir gently.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables and serve.

title: broccoli with bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; lay on paper towel to drain fat and crumble.
Cut up broccoli into bite size pieces.
Add chopped onion and mix the Miracle Whip thoroughly, then add the cheese. Refrigerate for about 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Cut into chunks.
Slightly cook broccoli.
Butter casserole dish.
Put broccoli in the bottom, then layer with chicken.
Mix other ingredients and layer on top of chicken.
Top with grated cheese, then add 1/4 stick butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add all ingredients, except kidney beans. Simmer.
Add beans 10 minutes before serving.

title: old fashioned biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits in pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over biscuits.
Stir together.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato cabbage soup
directions: Chop cabbage into small pieces.
Chop bacon into 1-inch pieces and fry until crisp.
Drain off fat; reserve 1 tablespoon.
Place reserved fat in saucepan.
Add vegetables, seasonings and water. Cover and heat to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir flour into evaporated milk.
Gradually add evaporated milk-flour mixture to vegetables. Stir constantly.
Add butter.
Cook until slightly thickened. Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, margarine, flour, pineapple and bread, broken into pieces.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, add onions, mushrooms and salt.
Cook until onions are done.
Add sour cream and set aside.
Bring water to boil with bouillon cubes.
Add rice.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well blended.
Press mixture in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together, stirring until well blended over very low heat.
Spread evenly over Rice Krispies.

title: crab muffins
directions: Line English muffins on a broiler pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on English muffins and broil.
Cut into quarters.
Great appetizer!

title: cleaning solution
directions: Mix together.
Keep out of reach of children.

title: slumber party snack(in the microwave)
directions: Combine butter, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, onion salt, and Ranch dressing powder in a small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave uncovered for 30 seconds and stir.
In a separate large microwave-safe bowl, combine cereals, pretzels, puffed rice, and nuts.
Pour sauce over mix and stir thoroughly.
Microwave (covered) on HIGH for five minutes, stirring after each minute. Cool until crispy and store in tupperware until ready to serve.

title: easy raspberry punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water and stir
until dissolved. Add to 1 gallon container the Jell-O (mixed with hot water), Kool-Aid (dry), lemonade (thawed) and sugar.
Add water and stir until dissolved. Serve over ice garnished with fresh fruit, if you like.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place the beef in soup kettle with 2 1/2 quarts of water.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt, pepper, celery leaves and 1 chopped onion. Combine bay leaves, oregano and thyme.
Tie in a cheesecloth bag and drop into kettle with meat.
Cover and simmer for at least 3 hours.
Remove celery leaves.
Remove meat from bones; cut into bite size pieces and add to stock.
Then add potatoes, carrots, green beans, cabbage, chopped onion and 1 tablespoon of salt. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add 2 cups water, tomatoes, sugar, corn, lima beans and 1 1/2 tablespoons salt.
Cook for 1 hour.
Remove cheesecloth spice bag before serving.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: Melt butter and add next 7 ingredients.
Add a little water if dry.
Score hot dogs lengthwise but not all the way through. Stuff hot dogs with bread mixture.
Wrap with bacon.
Broil 4 inches from heat until done.
Serve with mustard.
Serves 8.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, egg, margarine and nuts until crumbly.
Pat mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together eggs, cream cheese, sugar, coconut.
Spread mixture over top of crumb layer and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Boil rhubarb, sugar and pineapple for 10 minutes.
Add Jell-O and boil for 2 more minutes. Remove from heat.
Pour into containers and cool.
Keep in refrigerator or freezer.

title: barbecue beef burgers(makes 1 nesco or 3 gallons)
directions: Brown meat slowly in shortening with chopped onion and green pepper until crumbly, but no hard. Combine remaining ingredients and add to the meat. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt
butter in cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix in butter. Layer cherries, pineapple and nuts. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/4-inch loaf pans well.
In a large bowl with fork, mix the first 8 ingredients.
In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs, squash and salad oil until blended.
Stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Pour batter into greased pans.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool loaves in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on racks.

title: dressing
directions: Use enough broth to make mush.
Add salt and pepper before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meatballs in beer sauce
directions: Soak bread cubes in 1/2 cup beer.
Mix together with hamburger, cheese, pepper and garlic.
Form 32 meatballs.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Saute onion in oleo until tender.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, beef stock and 1 cup beer; simmer 10 minutes to thicken (salt lightly if desired).
Add meatballs and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls in a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Mix together all other ingredients and spread on crescent roll crust.
Top with any fresh (chopped fine) vegetables of your choice.
May also top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: crescent rolls with veggies
directions: Take crescent rolls and line bottom of pan.
Seal edges of rolls.
Mix cream cheese, mayo, Ranch dressing and horseradish. Spread on top of rolls.
Sprinkle rest of ingredients on top. Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes.

title: quick and easy chicken chow mein
directions: In large skillet, combine chicken, celery, onion, red pepper, bouillon, sugar, pepper, 1 1/2 cups water and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in bean sprouts.
In small bowl combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Over medium-high heat, carefully add to skillet mixture, stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat. Add water, macaroni, tomatoes and seasoning mix. Simmer covered 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Remove from heat and add 1/2 grated cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix soup, milk and salt, then add cheese.
Combine chicken and celery; add to all of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: black jam cake
directions: Mix and bake at 375°.
Makes a large layer cake.
First beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add creamed butter and jam, raisins and nuts.
Sift together flour and dry ingredients, then dissolve soda in milk and add to wet mixture and sift in dry ingredients. Add vanilla and bake.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: steak roll up
directions: Place onion, celery, pepper and bacon on steak an roll up like a jelly roll.
Secure with string or toothpicks.
Flour lightly and brown in heavy skillet.
Pour water on and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Good and easy.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to package directions through the kneading step.
Cover and let rest 30 minutes.

title: spicy mexican corn
directions: Drain picante sauce, reserving liquid.
Set vegetables aside. Measure reserved liquid, adding water to make 1/2 cup.
Combine reserved liquid and corn in saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until corn is tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Put in serving dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover until cheese melts.

title: pfeffernuesse("little peppernuts")
directions: Put the first four ingredients in a heavy saucepan and put on low heat until all ingredients are dissolved and sugar doesn't feel "grainy."
Remove from heat and add soda (dissolved in water), cinnamon, cloves and pepper. Stir in (or beat or pound) flour until dough becomes very stiff.
Divide dough and form into rolls, like sausages, about 1-inch in diameter.
Lay these on a flat pan, cover lightly with Saran Wrap to prevent drying, and chill until you find time to bake.
(Cookies have better flavor if chilled for a few days.)
To bake, cut into 1/2-inch slices and roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes. These are dunkin' cookies, and are best with coffee or milk.

title: carrot cake #2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend oil, sugar and eggs together. Add carrots and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Check for doneness by inserting toothpick.
Frost with cream cheese and powdered sugar frosting.

title: peanut butter pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil and remove to a plate.
Stir peanut butter and soup into drippings while gradually adding water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Add pork chops, onion and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: whole wheat hamburger buns
directions: Combine whole wheat flour and yeast; set aside.
Combine water, oil, sugar and salt.
Add eggs; beat all together for 3 minutes.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir in white flour by hand. Cover; let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down; let rest for 5 minutes. Shape into balls and press flat.
Place on greased cookie or baking sheet.
Cover; let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini relish salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sauce mix and sugar.
Add zucchini, green peppers and onions.
Toss lightly.
Chill before serving. Makes 6 cups.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter, then add other ingredients and stir.
Add about 2 1/2 pounds uncooked chicken.
Cook at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
(Cook uncovered for last 15 minutes.)

title: baked red rice
directions: Heat to boiling the tomato paste, water, bacon grease, onion and bell pepper.
You may prefer to saute onion and pepper in bacon grease first.
Remove from heat; stir in rice and sausage. Put in casserole dish and bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°. Take out and stir up; cover and cook for 30 minutes more.

title: pickled zucchini sticks
directions: Toss zucchini with salt.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Drain liquid from zucchini.

title: cran-apricot loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, eggs and oil.
Stir in cranberry mixture.
Grease eight (3 x 6-inch) loaf pans.
Divide batter among pans.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Melt preserves in a saucepan over low heat.
Remove the breads from pans and place on wire racks.
Brush with the preserves.
Cool 1 to 2 hours.
These may be wrapped and frozen for up to 3 months. These make great gifts at Christmas time.

title: cafe mexicano
directions: Heat water, brown sugar, chocolate, cloves and cinnamon to boiling in 3-quart saucepan; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in coffee.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Strain coffee through 4 thicknesses of cheesecloth.

title: ka-bobs
directions: Marinate at least 24 hours.

title: barbecue snack mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in jellyroll pan.
Melt butter or margarine.
Stir in barbecue seasoning, brown sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over ingredients in jellyroll pan and stir.
Bake for 45 minutes at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes. Pour on wax paper to cool.
Yield:
9 cups.

title: chocolate oatmeal surprise
directions: Combine sugar, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Combine cream cheese with sour cream.
Spread on the bottom of a 9-inch square microwave casserole dish.
Spread salsa on top, then sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave until cheese on top is melted.
Serve with potato or taco chips.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix catsup, chili sauce, horseradish and Tabasco sauce; shake well.
Arrange shrimp on lettuce; cover with sauce, cooked for servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, add sugar and continue beating. Add chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.

title: tropical pork salad
directions: Combine pork, rice, green pepper and celery in bowl.
Drain pineapple chunks; reserve 2 tablespoons juice. Add pineapple chunks to salad ingredients.
Combine and mix salad dressing, pineapple juice, ginger and salt; mix well.
Pour over salad ingredients; toss lightly to coat evenly.
Cover.
Chill well. Serve on salad greens.
Garnish with mint or watercress.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Stir by hand.
Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, chocolate bits or nuts (if using). Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes if using an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes if using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut after the brownies have been out of the oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 18 brownies.

title: bea's chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and water in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/4 package onion soup.
Lay chicken on top and sprinkle with rest of dry onion soup.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: fish casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In saucepan, stir undrained tomatoes, onions and taco mix.
Add macaroni and green pepper strips.
Bring mixture just to boiling and pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put fish on mixture and spoon some sauce over it.
Bake covered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle cheese over fish and bake 5 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pizza casserole
directions: * Sausage or bacon should be cooked and drained.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 pies.

title: spinach-roll meat loaf
directions: Omitting spinach for now, mix above ingredients well.
Spray a sheet of waxed paper with Pam or any vegetable spray.
Place meat mixture on paper and spread about 3/4-inch thick.
Press spinach on top of meat mixture.
Begin rolling mixture by lifting wax paper with both hands until meat rolls looks like a jelly roll (with spinach instead of jelly).
Pinch ends and place seam side down.
Sprinkle with paprika; score the top of the roll and place in baking dish or pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° after 10 minutes.
Bake for an additional 25 minutes.
Cover with a tent of foil, turn oven off and allow meat to remain in oven for an additional 10 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Dump rolls in sheath cake pan, and straighten them some. Sprinkle pudding mix (dry) over top.
Add sprinkle of cinnamon. Melt 1 stick of butter.
Mix with brown sugar and pecans.
Pour over rolls.
Cover with foil and let rise on the counter overnight.
Next morning, bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain and mash squash.
Mix with other ingredients.
Top with cracker crumbs and a little of the cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and carrots until tender and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Put in a buttered casserole with crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate raisin nut clusters
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass bowl, place chocolate bits, peanuts and raisins.
Cover; microwave at Low 4 to 5 minutes, or until chocolate melts.
Stir mixture; drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 24 pieces.

title: easy lasagna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. In pan you cooked noodles in, combine cream cheese and milk.
Cook over very low heat until well blended.
Stir in garlic salt and noodles.
Pour into Pam sprayed baking dish.

title: manicotti
directions: Crumble ground beef; cook and drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, water and 1 Tbsp. salt.
In another bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, Parmesan, eggs, pepper, 1 1/2 cup Mozzarella and 1/2 tsp. salt. Stuff uncooked manicotti with cheese filling.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, pour 1/2 of meat sauce, arrange manicotti in single layer.
Add remainder of meat sauce to cover.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Cover and cook 1 and 1/2 hours at 325°. (Check at 1 hour.)

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and apple cider vinegar the night before and refrigerate.
This will be the dressing.

title: overnite salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: sugar "cutout" cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar, eggs, flavoring and food coloring until fluffy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together in a separate bowl.
Combine the 2 mixtures and chill for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400° and roll dough 1/8 inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Cut with a cookie cutter and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake just until cookies are set (about 6 minutes).
Makes about 3 dozen.
Cool cookies and ice them or put different colors of sugar on before baking.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix lemon juice, garlic and olive oil in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss well.

title: cheese baked chicken
directions: Chop bread and olives.
Add to grated cheese.
Add other seasoning.
Dip chicken in butter and roll in crumb mix.
Coat thoroughly.
Put on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Go to store and buy box mix.
Substitute whipping cream in dairy box for milk.
Makes a fluffy cheese cake.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix crushed cereal, margarine and sugar. Pat in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes; cool. Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Slice bananas and arrange on crust.
Spread pudding over bananas; top with pineapple to edges of pan.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, garnish with cherries and whole cereal.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set overnight or several hours.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Combine corn, onion, green pepper and pimento.
Beat eggs slightly, then stir in sugar and salt. Smooth a little of the milk into the flour, then blend in the remaining milk.
Combine corn, eggs and milk mixture.
Add melted butter; turn into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: beef roast sandwiches
directions: Brown roast on both sides; sprinkle lemon juice over top and cover with water to top of roast and add bouillon cubes.
Cover and cook at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until roast can be broken apart with a fork.

title: bear roast
directions: Cover meat with salt, pepper and flour.
In Dutch oven or roasting pan, brown meat in bacon drippings.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 4 1/2 hours or until tender, turning meat every hour.
Serves 4 to 6.
Preparation Time:
5 hours.

title: chinese lobster sauce
directions: Brown hamburg; drain off fat.
Add beaten eggs and stir well. Add garlic powder and sugar.
Mix together soy sauce, Gravy Master and cornstarch with small amount cold water to a paste.
Add to hamburg and mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: carrot peanut sandwiches
directions: Grind together raw carrots, peanuts and onion.
Add mayonnaise and mix.
Serve on whole wheat bread.
Add lettuce, if desired.

title: holiday cereal cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and milk; bring to a full boil. Stir 2 additional minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips and butter until chips are completely melted. Stir in cereal.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill.

title: rotel frog's legs
directions: Salt frog legs generously.
Brown in skillet and remove. Blend flour and oil in skillet, brown.
Add onion, garlic, bell pepper and celery.
Mix thoroughly.
Add tomato sauce and Ro-Tel. Stir and add frog legs.
Cover and simmer until frog legs are tender.
Just before serving, add onions.
You may serve over rice.

title: ms. eunice's tea cakes
directions: Measure sifted flour; add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add vanilla. Add flour alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition. Chill dough overnight.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Prick tops of each cookie with fork to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 10 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: mama's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, drain and mash.
Mix squash with soup, sour cream, carrot and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach salad mold
directions: Drain peaches.
Heat juice to boiling.
Soften gelatin in lemon juice.
Dissolve in hot juice and cool.
Mash cream cheese and blend in mayonnaise and salt.
Stir in gelatin and whipped cream.
Fold in celery and sliced peaches.
Turn into ring mold. Chill until firm.
May be garnished with sliced peaches and maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over oleo.
Do not stir!
Pour 1 can fruit over ingredients evenly.
Sprinkle cinnamon, if desired.
Do not stir! Cook about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pomander
directions: Push cloves in the fruit so that the heads touch each other. Use push pin to start the holes.
When fruit is covered, tie ribbon around fruit.
Makes great gifts.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Stir in the next 3 ingredients.
Spread this mixture over the ham slices.
Roll up, starting with short side.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Chill.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Then make 24 meatballs.
Place in hot skillet and brown on all sides.
While meatballs are browning, dissolve 3 beef bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water.
Then pour over meatballs and simmer 30 minutes. Remove meatballs from pan and mix 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup milk together and add to beef broth.
Cook until thick, then pour over meatballs and serve hot.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Place rack in Dutch oven, wok or roasting pan with tight cover. Fill pan with hot water to within 1/4 inch of rack.
During cooking, add hot water to proper level.

title: ham loaf or rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Using 1/2 cup measure, form individual rolls or make as a loaf.
Place in pan and cover with sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Peel and cut apples small.
Chop nuts.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, egg and vanilla together.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown and crisp on top.
Remove from oven and cool.
Mixture will drop.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Melt oleo in water and boil.
Remove and add flour, stirring until it forms a ball.
Beat eggs one at a time.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese.
Gradually add milk to smooth consistency.
Stir in pudding; beat for 2 minutes.
Spread over cooled puff.
Top with whipped topping and fresh fruit.

title: stephanie's oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix dressing, soy sauce and ginger root.
Pour over wings and bake at 350° until tender.
(Marinate in sauce if preferred.)

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in small saucepan.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: cabbage bean soup
directions: In a 5 quart pot, brown beef, sausage, onion and bell pepper. Drain if necessary.
Add about 4 cups of water, beans, potatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to low and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Add cabbage and continue to cook until potatoes are tender and cabbage is done.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon dessert cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Dissolve lemon Jello in boiling water. Set aside to cool. In a large bowl, combine cake mix and corn oil. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add cooled lemon Jello to batter and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300 ° and bake 30 minutes longer. In a medium mixing bowl, combine powdered sugar with lemon juice and mix well. Remove cake and pierce all over with a 2 tined fork. Spread icing over cake while cake is hot.

title: berry cloud dessert
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy.
Beat in 1 3/4 cups sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until stiff and glossy.
Very important, do not underbeat.
Spread in pan and bake for 60 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Leave meringue in oven with door closed about 12 hours or overnight.

title: quick chicken and scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook onion in oil in 10-inch skillet about 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until tender.
Stir in water, milk, potatoes, sauce mix, chicken and paprika.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in green beans and cheese.
Cook about 10 minutes or until beans are heated through and cheese is melted.

title: cheese-chive biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; cut in 1/4 cup margarine with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in cheese and chives.
Add milk gradually, stirring just until moistened.
Shape into a ball.
Roll dough to 3/4-inch thickness on a floured surface.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cutter; place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Combine melted margarine and water; brush over tops of biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sliced potatoes in lightly salted water until tender; drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Drain juice from pineapple; add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Mix together the sugar and flour.
Add liquid and cook until it boils.
Add crushed pineapple and butter.
Pour over potatoes in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat eggs; add 1/2 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Brown 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet.
Add to other mix that has been heated, stirring and cooking slowly.
When thick, put in baked pie shell. Top with meringue and brown.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass baking dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in a large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: company can't wait casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add soup and mixed vegetables. Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook at 400° for 20 minutes.
Delicious served with slaw and corn muffins.
Serves 6.

title: avocado-crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except crabmeat in mixer or blender. Mix.
Pour into bowl.
Gently fold in crabmeat.
Chill for a few hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger stew
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Add tomatoes, carrots, celery, potatoes, water, rice, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender. Uncover. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer or until thickened.

title: zesty pineapple relish
directions: The heat of the chili is in the seeds and ribs.
Remove them before mincing (wear rubber gloves to do so).

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add to melted butter and beaten eggs.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Chill until center is firm enough to cut.

title: souffle-topped herbed chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish (or place each portion in an individual baking dish).
Sprinkle green onions and tarragon on top.
Dot with butter, seasoned with salt and pepper. Add wine.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Beat egg white to stiff peaks.
Fold in mayonnaise. Spoon mixture on top of chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes more or until light brown.
Makes 8 servings (316 calories per serving).

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Cook peas as directed on package; drain.
Shake Italian dressing, sugar and crushed red pepper in tightly covered container.
Combine cooked peas, dressing, celery, green pepper, red pepper, onions, parsley, salt and pepper.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.

title: kahlua
directions: Pour sugar into boiling water; boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in instant coffee.
Add vanilla, one teaspoon at a time.
Mix until everything is dissolved.
Place back over heat and bring to boil.
Remove from heat again and allow to cool several minutes.
Stir in vodka.
Split vanilla bean and place in 1/2 gallon container.
Pour mixture into container.
Cap and ferment at room temperature at least 2 weeks.

title: greek egg and lemon soup
directions: Cook the rice in the stock until tender.
Beat the eggs until light, adding lemon juice slowly while beating.
Gradually add some hot stock to the eggs, stirring constantly.
Combine with remaining stock.
Stir over low heat until slightly thickened.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve garnished with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: never fail meringue
directions: In saucepan, combine above ingredients except for egg whites. Cook until thickened and clear.
Cool.

title: katherine's spinach salad dressing(makes 1 cup)
directions: Stir daily with wooden spoon.

title: lazy cabbage rolls
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Chop cabbage in large pieces and place in bottom of dish.
Brown beef and onion.
Stir in rice and salt.
Pour all over cabbage.
Mix soup and water and pour over meat mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: turtles
directions: On greased wax paper, place 4 to 5 pecans in shape of turtle. Place 1 caramel on top of each pile.
Place in microwave 2 minutes, until caramel is softened; press around pecans. Microwave almond bark 1 1/2 minutes on High and stir.
Continue until bark is melted.

title: (costue) squaw bread(authentic osage recipe)
directions: Boil together corn syrup and brown sugar and add maple flavoring.
Take off fire and beat in bacon grease.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Butter shallow casserole.
Layer the ingredients in the order listed.
Between layers, season with garlic and salt and bake at 350° until bubbly and hot, about 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine flour, cottage cheese, eggs and salt in bowl; mix well.
Add butter, cheese and spinach; mix well.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chewie noelle
directions: Melt butter and pour into a 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add sugar and nuts.
Stir in eggs and vanilla. Carefully pour batter over butter in pan.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on wax paper on a rack, then invert pan onto this.
When cool, sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: mexican rice and sausage
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add picante sauce, water and green chilies.
Bring to a boil; then add rice.
Bring to simmer. Add smoked sausage that has been sliced.
Cover and simmer until rice is done.
Stir occasionally.

title: old fashion chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Take 3/4 cup sugar; add the flour and cocoa to sugar.
Add the mixture to beaten egg yolks; stir in milk slowly. Cook over medium heat, stirring continually, until thickened.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil and stir well.
Add eggs (one at a time) and add carrots, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy salsa
directions: Dice chilies; then combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix on low speed, until desired consistency.
Keep in a covered container in refrigerator.

title: chinese pork chop recipe
directions: Spread the dry rice evenly into a greased roaster.
Sprinkle the seasoning packet over the top of the rice.
In a large bowl, stir together the vegetables, soup, water and mushrooms.
Pour this over the rice.
Arrange the pork chops on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients in frying pan.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rabbit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out the bottom crust; put in pie shell.
In a separate bowl, put rabbit meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix together; put mixture in pie shell.
Roll out top crust.
Make slits in crust.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 11 to 12 minutes, or until set; cookies will be slightly moist in center.
Do not overbake.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: lasagna with raw noodles
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; mix all ingredients except last 5, together.
Let simmer 15 minutes (will be thin).
Combine Mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese, egg and cottage cheese.
Put a layer of sauce on the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan, then a layer of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese mixture, dry cheese and end with Mozzarella cheese mixture.
Make this up 12 to 24 hours prior to baking.
Put in fridge for 12 to 24 hours.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Uncover last 10 minutes.

title: cheesy green onion quiche
directions: Line pie plate or quiche dish with pastry.
(May use frozen, deep dish pie crust.)
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with fork. Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove and gently prick with fork. Return to oven.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Mix onion, celery, rice, butter and broccoli together in a casserole dish.
Pour soup and Cheez Whiz over all and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy baked ziti
directions: Partially cook noodles (3/4 of required time). In baking dish layer sauce, noodles, cheese; repeat. Top with a little sauce and mozzarella. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil and bake 15 minutes.

title: dawg gone
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease two 6 cornstick baking pans or one 12 stick pan.
Place in oven to heat.
Cut frankfurters into 1/4-inch slices.

title: mexican bean dip(ole)
directions: Blend all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with nacho chips for dipping.

title: auntie claire's world famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Whip shortening, adding both sugars.
Add lightly beaten eggs, hot water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients along with chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop large chunks of dough onto a greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot almond coffee cake
directions: Cream soft butter.
Add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 1 minute after each egg.
Add dry ingredients, beating only until mixed.
Fold in sour cream and almond extract. Flour and grease pan (Bundt or tube).
Add 1/3 of batter to pan. Put half preserves and almonds on top of batter.
Put almost all remaining batter on top and remaining preserves and almonds.
Add rest of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: potato salad
directions: Prepare in order given, add paprika, celery salt and onion seasoning before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all but 1 cup cheese together and spread into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and some paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Place beef and onion in baking dish and pour rice over it. Mix other ingredients and pour over rice. Cook at 375° for 1 hour covered with tinfoil.

title: jambalaya
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil in large saucepan over high heat; add sausage, cook 2 to 3 minutes. Remove chicken and sausage from saucepan; set aside.
Cook onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in same saucepan over medium heat until tender-crisp.
Stir in rice, red pepper, broth and reserved chicken and sausage; bring to a boil.
Simmer covered 30 minutes. Stir in green onions and tomatoes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: favorite dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast in mixing bowl.
Heat milk, water and margarine to lukewarm.
Gradually add to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour; beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make dough and knead for 2 to 3 minutes or until elastic.
Make out in rolls and let rise for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: easy cheese bars
directions: Mix together and pat into 9 x 13. Sprinkle 1/2 c. chopped nuts over this.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder, salt and soda; add nuts.
Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat and add sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture a small amount at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Spread in an ungreased 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool, then cut in bars.
Makes 16 to 24 bars.

title: honeymooner's cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together. Pour over melted margarine.
(Do not stir.)
Pour fruit over all. (Do not stir.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: thanksgiving pie
directions: Hugging is healthy; it helps our body's immune system, it keeps you healthier, it cures depression, reduces stress and induces sleep.
It's invigorating and rejuvinating.
It has no unpleasant side effects and hugging is nothing less than a miracle drug. Hugging is all natural.
It is organic, naturally sweet.
It has no pesticides, no preservatives and no artificial ingredients.
And it is 100% wholesome.
Hugging is practical.

title: christmas decorations
directions: Mix well, roll out on waxed paper.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutter.
Punch one hole in each so thread can be inserted later.
Set aside to dry for several days.
Use on Christmas tree for fragrance.

title: pumpkin pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Blend together in blender to make really smooth.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Mix all together and cook all day on low in crock-pot.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in oil.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain spinach and set aside.
Reserve liquid. Add water to make 1 cup.
Stir spinach liquid and next 5 ingredients into meat mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with meat sauce and little more shredded cheese, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: london chicken(serves 12)
directions: Brown chicken in butter, then brown the mushrooms.
Place chicken in large casserole. Mix the soups and pour over chicken. Place mushrooms on top.
Refrigerate. When ready to bake, cover the casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham and broccoli chowder
directions: Mix flour and water.
Add remaining ingredients to soup pot. Cook slowly all day.
At serving time, stir in 1 cup light cream.

title: turkey crescent almondine
directions: In a large saucepan, add first 8 ingredients.
Cook until hot and bubbly.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: plantation okra
directions: Boil okra in salt water for 10 minutes; drain.
Fry bacon and remove from skillet, but retain for garnish.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of Pyrex dish.
Combine flour and sugar and sprinkle on pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine crackers and margarine and spread on top of casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: california rice casserole
directions: Put in casserole (except cheese) and cover the top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit ice cream
directions: Chill in ice cream freezer.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and cut into small pieces.
Layer bite-size shreds of lettuce, then onion, cauliflower and bacon in a large salad bowl.
Mix last 4 ingredients and spread on it.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: carrot-apple salad
directions: Combine carrots, apples and raisins.
Add honey to yogurt and add to carrots, apples and raisins.
Stir to blend.

title: broccoli bake with macaroni
directions: Put water in kettle and bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and boil 6 minutes.
Drain.
Mix broccoli, macaroni and cottage cheese together in bowl.
Set aside.
Coat an 11 x 7-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Spread broccoli mixture in the dish.
Beat eggs; add pepper, paprika and dry mustard to the beaten eggs and pour this over broccoli.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all together. Top with a few of the pecans and cherries. Refrigerate.

title: champagne punch
directions: Chill all liquid ingredients.
Mix just before serving, stirring only once.
Pour over ice.
Float sliced lemons and oranges on top of punch.
Serves 24.

title: apple butter from blender
directions: Blend all
ingredients	except	apples in blender.
Add 1/2 the apples.
Cover,
run
on high speed until smooth.
Add remaining apples, cover
and
run
on high speed until smooth. Cook mixture in saucepan until thick (about 30 to 40 minutes). Seal in sterilized jars.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Put last 4 items in cheesecloth and simmer 20 minutes in the cider.
Enjoy!

title: beef stew
directions: Saute the onions with the celery.
Add salt and pepper to dredging flour.
Brown on all sides in hot shortening.
Mix tomato puree and hot water; pour over meat and onions.
Add bay leaf. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer until all ingredients are done, approximately 1 hour, on low heat; stir often.
Remove bay leaf.
The liquid may be a little too thick. If so, add a little more water.
It's supposed to be thicker than soup.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes about 10 minutes.
Melt margarine and onion together until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Slice potatoes and put in ungreased casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all together.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serves 6.

title: s'more bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the butter in the pan and melt in oven for 3 minutes.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly.
Pour on sweetened condensed milk evenly. Sprinkle on the chocolate chips and then the marshmallows.
Press down with your fingers.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool completely and cut in squares.

title: scrumptious spaghetti
directions: Pour the Prego into your pot; add the tomato paste and mix. Cut up the whole tomatoes, then add to the sauce.
Semi-precook your sausage (cut into bite size pieces first), then add to the sauce.
Let simmer on low for approximately 30 minutes or until your liking.
Stir frequently.
Cook noodles and enjoy.

title: egg nog
directions: Blend well. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
For chocolate, omit vanilla and add chocolate syrup.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Add milk to thicken to consistency of regular corn bread.
Bake in a greased pan until brown.
Serve with Spanish tomato rice and fried beans.

title: powdered sugar cake
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar gradually and continue creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, and continue creaming.
Sift the flour and fill the empty sugar box; add gradually and beat until smooth. Add lemon flavoring.

title: rice idith
directions: Rub 1 1/2-quart dish with a small amount of butter.
Pour in all ingredients (including rest of butter).
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: sunset salad
directions: Squeeze the lemon until you have 1/2 cup of juice.
In a medium-size bowl, combine juice and carrots.
Prepare jello according to package directions.
Add lemon juice and carrots. Refrigerate until jello is firm.
Serve on slice of lettuce.

title: edna's sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat.
Thicken with cornstarch and water mixture.

title: sunday morning quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs and next 6 ingredients.
Add cheeses and sausage; fold together.
Pour into ungreased quiche dish and arrange red pepper into pretty design. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until a knife, inserted in center, comes out clean.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, melt butter.
Stir in sour cream and both cans of corn including liquids.
Add corn bread mix.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until surface is browned.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt in square Pyrex dish the butter.
Make a batter with next ingredients, except sugar.
Mix with a spoon.
Pour batter over butter.
Do not stir; pour choice of fruit filling.
Then sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: everlasting apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in covered 5-quart plastic ice cream container in refrigerator for up to 8 weeks.
Bake muffins for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.
You can bake them right away, too.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers; do not peel.
Alternate with onion and pack in bowl and place in refrigerator (covered).
Mix sugar, salt and mustard, then add vinegar, celery seed, pepper and salad oil.
Mix salad oil 1/2 at a time so it will mix up well.
Pour the mixture over cucumbers and onion and refrigerate until time to use.
Make night before so it will season; will keep for 1 week.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat tomato soup, cream cheese and mayo until smooth.
Combine Knox gelatine and water and pour into soup mixture.
Add shrimp, celery and onion. Pour into an oiled mold and allow to set. Serve with crackers.

title: poor man's syrup
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Boil (5 to 10 minutes) until completely dissolved.
Remove from fire, add butter or margarine.
Serve hot over hot pancakes.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Cook onion in hot butter until soft.
Add water, catsup and seasonings.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add frankfurters; cook over low heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Clean cranberries.
Combine sugar and wine in saucepan.
Heat on medium.
Stir to boil.
Add cranberries, cinnamon and orange zest.
Heat on high to boiling.
Simmer, partially covered, until berries burst (about 10 minutes).
Remove cinnamon and orange zest.
Pour into serving container and put in refrigerator until cool and hardened.

title: perfect potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly and dry. Apply thin coat of vegetable oil to potato skins.

title: fruit cake balls
directions: Blend together the margarine, egg and powdered sugar.
Add drained, chopped cherries, dates and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon into graham cracker crumbs and roll.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl; stir until well blended.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Cut into bite size serving pieces.
May be served hot or cold.

title: uncle carroll's fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash the tomatoes and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Dip in eggs, then dip in cornmeal or flour that has been seasoned in salt and pepper, coating both sides.
Fry in hot oil several minutes on each side until crisp.

title: whipped cream salad
directions: Whip
cream until almost stiff.
Add sugar until sweet. Finish whipping
cream until completely stiff.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides of 2-quart saucepan.
Combine milk and sugar and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and quickly add marshmallow cream, peanut butter, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir until just blended.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs together until creamy.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake paper in a muffin tin.
Fill 1/2 full with cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 20.

title: cream of wild rice soup
directions: Prepare wild rice according to basic directions on package. Saute bacon to extract drippings, then add butter, onion, green pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Continue sauteing until vegetables begin to soften.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add chicken broth, stirring to make a smooth mixture.

title: apricot cream
directions: Soak apricots for 3 to 4 hours.
Add orange juice to sugar. Add apricots.
Simmer on low fire to well cooked.
Cool mixture. Put mixture in blender and puree.
Add whipping cream.
Arrange layers of apricot cream and ice cream.
Decorate with nuts.

title: greek salad
directions: Cut lettuce bite size.
Medium chop tomatoes. Thin slice onion.
Add olives and Feta cheese.
Toss while adding virgin olive oil to coat salad.
Squeeze lemon juice over salad to taste; toss again.

title: green rice
directions: Cook 2 cups rice.
Cook broccoli by directions on pkg.
Mix cooked rice with mushroom soup, broccoli, cheese, and melted butter.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: put-back potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut potatoes in half and remove potato from shell.
Place pulp in large mixing bowl.
Place shells on a cookie sheet.

title: cheese ball
directions: When cheeses are soft enough to shape, mix with remaining ingredients except parsley.
Form into ball.
Roll in parsley flakes and/or chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: lickity-split cocoa cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Stir with a spoon or wire whisk until batter is smooth and ingredients are well blended.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Frost as desired.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugars and egg together.
Add remaining ingredients (except the peanut butter cups) and mix well.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in sugar and put into tiny muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Take out of oven and push peanut butter cups into center of cookies.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In bottom of baking dish, line with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Place a can of asparagus (drain the juice and set aside) on top of the Ritz crackers.
Combine the juice and the cream of mushroom soup together; pour over the asparagus.
Top with grated cheese and bake until it bubbles for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Mix the soup and sour cream.
In buttered casserole, layer the broccoli and soup mixture and 1 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.
Can be prepared the day ahead and cooked later.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift with baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening.
Add milk to form a soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured board for a few seconds.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick. Fold over so dough is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter. Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes at 450°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake in oblong baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini-nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dill pickle relish
directions: Chop cukes, sweet green peppers, sweet red peppers and onion. Dissolve salt into water; pour over vegetables.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours; drain thoroughly.
Combine white vinegar, dry mustard and dill seed in a pan; heat until boiling.
Add vegetables; bring to boil again.
Pack hot in hot jars.
(You can add 1 head of dill to each jar before adding vegetables, if you desire.)
Process in water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let sit
minutes.
Sift dry ingredients. Add shortening and mix until
crumbly.
Add milk and yeast mixture.
Mix well and cover bowl.
Refrigerate	at
least
hour
(or overnight is better). Roll
out
on floured board. Cut and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring ingredients to boil. Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Remove from heat and when pan is lukewarm, add 1 quart 100 proof vodka and 3 teaspoons vanilla. Stir and cool. Best to store for 3 weeks for better flavor.

title: cooked spaghetti
directions: Bring water to
a
boil.
Break
spaghetti
in half and drop in the boiling water.
Boil until tender; drain and rinse with cool water.
Add to the meat balls and tomato sauce for a delicious meat ball and spaghetti dinner.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Flavor will improve if refrigerated for awhile.

title: mock crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream; mix.
Add crab, onion and garlic salt.
Mix together.
Sprinkle paprika on top and refrigerate.
Great as a dip with crackers or chips.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cut up spinach. Drain well. Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve in a hollowed out round loaf of bread.
Use bread cubes and crackers for dipping.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Make brine with sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer 15 minutes.
In each hot jar, put grape leaf, head of dill, garlic clove,
bay leaf and mustard seed.
Pack cukes into jar, top with another head of dill.
Fill jar with hot brine and seal.

title: lamb stew with green peppers
directions: Prepare lamb chunks and have ready, along with the onion and mushrooms.
Have heavy casserole ready.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all together real well.
Makes 1 cup.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice.
Add enough water to the juice to make 1 cup.
Blend butter, flour and sugar in a saucepan. Gradually stir in pineapple juice.
Cook until thickened over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add tidbits.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with marshmallows.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, blend cheese with fork until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, 1/2 cup nuts, onion and seasoned salt.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining nuts. Wrap in foil or plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add sausage and saute until brown, about 8 minutes. Transfer sausage to bowl, using a slotted spoon.
Reserve sausage drippings.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken pieces with cayenne pepper. Add to skillet with sausage drippings.
Saute until brown and cooked through, turning occasionally, about 5 minutes. Transfer chicken to bowl with sausage.

title: peach chews
directions: Combine peaches and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Chop peaches and toss with flour.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in egg yolks and extracts.
Gradually mix in flour-peach mixture. Shape in small balls.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 325° about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: christmas pralines
directions: Blend sugar, salt and evaporated milk.
Cook to 332° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and pecan halves. Beat just until candy begins to thicken.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
(Work fast, for candy hardens quickly.)
Yields 1 1/2 dozen pralines.

title: canadian pork pie
directions: Combine ground pork, onions and water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour or until done.
Add spices, salt, pepper and potatoes.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, skim fat.
Fill double pie crust with filling.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
The longer it sits the better it tastes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Prepare cake as directed on box except substitute pineapple for water.
Stir in coconut and rum flavoring.
Pour into cake pans.
Bake at 350° or as directed on box.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Fill and frost layers with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then yolks (slightly beaten).
Add almond extract, then add enough flour, mixed with baking powder, to make a soft dough.
Chill several hours.
Roll and cut with cookie cutters; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sprinkles before baking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine
sugar,
margarine and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil
and
cook
14 to 16 minutes.	Remove and add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: special round steak
directions: Put roast in the bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Put cream of mushroom soup in casserole.
Pour 7-Up over all this.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours.
Check at 3 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Mix soups and water.
Add hamburger mix and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix spaghetti with this and put in a casserole; top with remaining cheese and bake in a moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water and 1 cup juice from fruit. Chill until set; whip cream cheese and jello together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add fruit and mix well.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: calico squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine the first five ingredients; add 1/2 tsp. salt.
Cover and cook until squash is tender, about 6 minutes. Drain well; set
aside.
Combine crumbs and butter; spoon half into a greased shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Combine soup, water chestnuts, carrot, mayonnaise, pimentos, sage, pepper and remaining salt; fold into squash mixture.
Spoon over crumbs. Sprinkle with cheese and the remaining crumb mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix the brown sugar, flour and water.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring while cooking.
Take off and add salt and lemon juice.
Return to cooking for 5 minutes more.
Take off and add butter and raisins.
Allow to stand before using.
Delicious with ham!

title: easy hot dog pizza
directions: Make pizza crust (dough) as directed on bread mix package. Spread dough on greased pizza pan, or flat pan.
Mix sugar, tomato sauce, garlic salt, red pepper and Worcestershire sauce in bowl, then spread over pizza crust.
Spread sliced hot dogs on crust, then the cheese.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt white chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add white chocolate, vanilla, flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Bake in 2 pans lined with waxed paper and greased at 350°.

title: raisin and nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Remove from hot water.
Let stand five minutes to partially cool.
Add salt, raisins and nut meats.
Blend well.
Drop from teaspoon onto a sheet of waxed paper.
Makes about 30 pieces.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, when cooked, debone and cube.
In boiling stock from chicken, cook spaghetti, pepper, onion, and celery.
Drain when tender.
Heat cheese and soup in microwave, add spaghetti and chicken.

title: mom's pecan pie(from the files of viola clark williams)
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cocoa cookies
directions: Mix sugar and oleo together.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts. Work like bread until it forms a soft dough.
Mold in hand with fingers making imprint.
Place on cookie sheet close together. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Dust with 10x sugar.

title: fruit and fibre cereal cookies
directions: Combine flour with soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter in large bowl.
Blend in sugar, honey, eggs and the flour mixture. Add cereal and mix thoroughly.

title: dream pineapple pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and crushed pineapple.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with pineapple chunks.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip if desired.

title: cookies 'n cream pie
directions: Pour half
and
half
into
large bowl, add pie filling, mix. Beat until
well
blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and crushed cookies.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
About
6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer, let stand
10 minutes to soften before serving.
Store leftover in freezer.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and cold water.
Cook to 242° on candy thermometer.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; add butter and peanuts.
Continue cooking to 292°.
Remove from heat and add 1 rounded teaspoonful baking soda.
Mix quickly and pour onto buttered pan or pans.
Cool slightly and pull until thin.
Cool. Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: fast chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan.
Stir with a fork until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Blend in milk.
Cook over medium heat; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly (work fast when you start to mix, it sets up fast; if it gets too hard, add a little milk.)
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato and add salt and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar and stir until it looks like pie crust.
Roll on sugared wax paper. Spread with peanut butter.
Roll and put in refrigerator.
Slice and serve when chilled.

title: ham cheese quiche
directions: Combine milk, mayonnaise, eggs and cornstarch; mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese come to room temperature.
Grate cheese and work all together.
Make small balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° or until light brown.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Cut shrimp down the back lengthwise with kitchen shears, being careful not to cut all the way through.
With shells intact, remove black veins, rinse and pat dry.
(If using frozen shrimp, start with this step.)
Melt butter with oil in a large skillet.
Add garlic and saute just until garlic is lightly golden.
Add shrimp; saute, shaking skillet and stirring 2 to 3 minutes, or just until shrimp is pink and firm.
Garnish with chopped parsley and lemon wedges.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Oil cookie pan.
Combine oats, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, raisins and nuts in a large bowl.
In another bowl, combine oil, apple juice and vanilla.
Pour liquid into dry ingredients. Stir until flour is absorbed.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Clean crab meat.
Mix with softened cream cheese and rest of ingredients.
Save enough Cheddar cheese for top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until bubbly.

title: killer cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Fill 20 to 22 cupcake pans with paper liners.
Melt
together
the
chocolate,
vanilla	and butter. Beat the eggs until thick and add sugar.
Beat in the flour.
Fold in	the
butter
chocolate	mixture.
Spoon
into prepared pans, filling 2/3 full.

title: chicken divan
directions: Spray a large oblong glass baking dish with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil 1 large package chicken thighs until done, prick clean of fat and skin and layer on bottom of pan.
Cook frozen chopped broccoli; drain and layer on top of chicken.
Mix the following separately:
mushroom soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry. Pour over the chicken and broccoli.
Layer with sharp Cheddar cheese; then layer with bread crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour, until bubbly.

title: michigan dried blueberry, macadamia nut and white chocolate cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Beat in the brown sugar and then the egg, orange peel and vanilla.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Add butter to zucchini and onions and saut until half tender (turns clear).
Then add mushrooms with some of the liquid and sugar.
Cook until done.
Very good.
Serve hot as a vegetable as soon as cooked.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Add strawberries. Add pineapple, nuts and bananas.
(I let the strawberries thaw first, they seem to mix better.)
After you have mixed the ingredients all together, pour half of the mixture into a 10 x 13-inch glass dish and set in the refrigerator.
Leave the other half of the mixture set at room temperature. When first layer is set, blend Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Spread over top
of set Jell-O, then add remaining Jell-O that has been setting at room temperature.
Return to refrigerator for top layer of Jell-O to set.

title: fish
directions: Dip fish in mill and fry.
When brown, take out.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together everything except apples with a mixer.
Stir in apples.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and frost.
Good with cream cheese frosting.

title: vichyssoise(otherwise known as potato leek soup)
directions: Chop the white part only of leeks.

Saute the leeks and onion in melted butter in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until onion is tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in potatoes and chicken broth. Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Put half the potato mixture in blender and blend at high speed until pureed.
Transfer to large bowl and repeat with remaining potato mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve cold or heat gently and serve warm.

title: viennese rice
directions: Melt butter, saute rice, onion and celery.
When nicely coated, add beef broth, mushrooms, and cover on low flame.
When finished, spoon in peas.
YUM, YUM, YUMI!

title: no bake "candy" cookies
directions: Put in kettle the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to boil for 4 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir in 6 cups oats, a cup at a time.
(Will start to set up like candy as mixture cools.)
Drop on wax paper by teaspoon.

title: supreme potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese together.
Spread into buttered casserole.
Spread corn flakes and melted butter on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spicy apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread apple pie filling in an 8-inch square pan.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread over apples.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serve plain or top with vanilla ice cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: tea refresher
directions: Boil loose leaf tea in water for 5 minutes.
Let sit 5 minutes and strain.
Add juice and sugar.
Keep in refrigerator.
Better after 12 hours in fridge.

title: poppy seed cakes
directions: Blend butter, sugar and flour.
Roll into a ball.
Flatten. Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Combine juices.
Place sherbet and ice cream in punch bowl and soften with wooden spoon.
Add juices, stirring sherbet and ice cream until partially melted.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serves 30.

title: chocoholic cheesecake
directions: *These are very difficult to find in the grocery store.
I use Oreo's instead.
Scrape off the white filling and roll the chocolate part between two pieces of wax paper with rolling pin to crush.

title: million dollar pie
directions: After all ingredients are mixed, pour into pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Bake in 9-inch pie dish.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven until light brown on top.

title: twice cooked corn
directions: Husk corn and set aside.
Into a large pan or pot, pour the water, milk and sugar; bring to a boil.
Now add the corn and cook for 3 minutes.
Drain corn, roll in melted butter and sprinkle with the chili powder.
(At this point, the corn can be left covered in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.)
Right before serving, cook on grill, directly over hot coals, for 2 minutes on each side.
Serves 8.

title: creamy beef bake
directions: Make Kraft dinner.
Set aside in large bowl.
Brown hamburg and onion in butter.
Drain fat.
Add soup and milk to hamburg and cook over medium heat, stirring to blend.
Add hamburg soup mixture to Kraft dinner in bowl, mixing all together.
Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a single layer in a large skillet. Combine orange juice, soy sauce, molasses, dry mustard, garlic powder, cinnamon and ginder. Pour over chicken. Bring to boil, lower heat. Cover and let simmer for 30 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Add green pepper, cook 5 minutes longer.

title: chocolate-covered cherry cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour and cocoa; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat the butter or margarine with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 minutes or until softened.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in melted butter and flour, making sure flour is mixed in well (not lumpy).
Stir in milk and corn.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Set in a shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife blade inserted in center comes out clean. Serves 4 to 5.

title: crab louis
directions: This salad is a
product
of
the
West Coast where the magnificent Pacific crab is often served in this way.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Mix together broccoli, chicken and mushroom soup or chicken soup and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and celery soup.
Pour over broccoli/chicken mixture. Top with Cheddar cheese and buttered crumbs.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: baked corn
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour.
Mix with other ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup of cheese for top.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 40 minutes or until it begins to brown and is rather firm.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in water and add strawberries.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Chill!

title: magic coconut squares(crunchy, tasty and fun.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan and place in oven to melt butter. Remove pan from oven and sprinkle crumbs over butter, pressing down with a fork.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs. Add layer of nuts and one of marshmallows. Drizzle condensed milk evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and drizzle with melted chocolate.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 48 bars.

title: west virginia hash
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Drain. Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour 3 times.
Last time, add baking powder.
Beat butter and Crisco until creamy.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy. Separate eggs; beat yolks and add to creamy mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon flavors.
Add flour and milk alternately and beat.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to mixture and beat until well mixed. Put in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, salt, pepper, soup, onions and sour cream.
Add 3 cups shredded cheese and mix.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: May substitute ground beef for sausage; use salt and pepper to season.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift the plain flour, self-rising flour and dash of salt.
Mix all the ingredients together with a mixer.
Mix well for about 10 to 15 minutes. The longer you beat it, the smoother the cake. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix milk and bran flakes together, let set for 5 minutes.
Add oil and eggs, mix well, add this with flour and sugar and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; boil until blended.
Cool.
Break saltines into small squares (quarters).
Place them into crust. Pour cooled syrup over them.
Cover with the other crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chops.
Stuff chops with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Separate egg whites and yolks; beat yolks.
Add milk.
Mix cocoa and vanilla.
Mix cocoa, 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt. Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Add wet egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Gradually add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into skillet with melted butter; cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool and place in prebaked pie shell.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Roll out one package of rolls and place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; spread over rolls.
Top with second package of rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Mix 1/2 cup powdered sugar with enough milk to dissolve sugar and drizzle over rolls when done.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except chili sauce and horseradish and shape into a ball or ring.
Mix chili sauce and horseradish, lemon juice and Worcestershire to taste.
Pour over crab mixture.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add mashed bananas.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add gelatin and let cool. Add buttermilk, pecans and topping.
Congeal.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Allow to cool.
Cut into halves, remove yolks and place in bowl.
Set egg whites aside.
In bowl with yolks, add relish, dressing and salt.
Mix.
Spoon mixture into egg whites. Serve.

title: chocolate peanutbutter pie
directions: First layer:
Beat softened cream cheese and syrup together until blended.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into baked pie crust.
Add crushed peanuts on top of first layer.

title: toffee
directions: Boil for 6 minutes.
Pour over nut crumbs on cookie sheet. Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Pour mixture over the carrots, green peppers and onions.
Let set at least 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.
Keeps up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until very light.
Add beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Sift flour and salt together and add to first mixture.
Add soda, vanilla and nutmeats.
Bake 1 hour in moderately slow oven (325°).
Makes one 9 x 5-inch loaf.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add ketchup, paste, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Stir until well blended.
Add pinto beans, undrained.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Add hot sauce, if desired.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Stir dry Jell-O into cottage cheese; let set in refrigerator 5 or 6 hours or overnight.
Stir in Cool Whip and drained oranges. Sprinkle nuts on top and let set until firm.

title: mrs. tidwell's coconut sweet potato pie
