directions: Prepare Pie Crust with high fluted edge.
Bake and cool. Combine in a bowl; Sweet Potatoes, Milk, Eggs, Sugar, Coconut, Pecans and Vanilla.
Pour into Pie Crust.
Microwave at Medium for 20 minutes or until center is almost set.
Let stand and cool.
Top with Whip Cream when serving.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter, then add rest of ingredients.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix together put in casserole dish. Put topping on top.

title: percolator punch
directions: Fill a 30-cup percolator with the juices and water.
Place everything else in the percolator basket.
Turn on percolator; allow the juices to go through the cycle. Serve hot.
Yields 24 cups.

title: bacon wrapped string beans
directions: Drain beans, reserving liquid.
For each bundle, wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around approximately 10 green beans.
Mix juice from green beans with remaining ingredients and pour over bundles. Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Peel cucumbers and onions.
Chop fairly fine in food processor.
Put vegetables in a large bowl and throw in the salt. Let sit for 1 hour.
Drain very well through sieve. Place in a deep kettle and add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Boil for about 10-15 minutes.
Ladle into sterile pint size jars and seal tightly.

title: skillet franks with barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings until tender. Add juice, catsup and chili powder.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add frankfurters and simmer 1/2 hour more.

title: fried pies
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Gently blend in Crisco with fingertips until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in buttermilk.
(Use more if necessary to make a stiff sticky dough.) Place heaping tablespoonfuls of dough onto floured sheet.
Sprinkle top with flour.
Lightly roll and press into round balls between hands.
With rolling pin, roll flat about 1/4-inch thick.
Drop in center of dough, one heaping tablespoonful filling, fold over and press ends together with fork.
Roll out all dough and fill all pies before starting to fry.
Deep fry in hot skillet of 1/2 Crisco and 1/2 Crisco oil until golden brown, turning once.

title: meat and cheese ball
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.
Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake as directed for layer cake and let cool.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Spread in an 8 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Mix butter, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer a large bowl with bananas, then wafers. Mix vanilla pudding mix according to package instructions. When pudding mixture is thick, add Eagle Brand milk and stir. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour over and through bananas and wafers until well coated. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry-nut bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans.
Stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
(Light handling is necessary for good texture.)
Spoon batter into two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.

title: taco dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Layer:
cream cheese, chili, olives and onion, cheeses.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Can be reheated in microwave.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: quiche
directions: Mix slightly beaten eggs with light cream and salt.
Cook onion about 5 minutes in 1 tablespoon butter; add onion, cheese and crumbled bacon to egg mixture.
Season with nutmeg, cayenne pepper and dash of ginger.
Precook pie shell for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into shell.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°; lower heat to 325° and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until center is firm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch glass cake pan or large casserole dish with vanilla wafers.
In a large bowl, combine condensed milk, milk and water.
Add pudding mixes; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread part of pudding mixture over vanilla wafers; add additional layers of wafers, bananas and pudding until gone, ending with pudding.
Chill thoroughly and refrigerate leftovers.

title: untossed salad
directions: Sprinkle spinach with a little salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer the first 6 ingredients` in bowl in given order.
Spread top with mayonnaise.
Be sure that the mayonnaise comes to the side of the dish to seal out air.
Top with cheese.
Do not toss!
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Spoon deeply to serve.

title: cheese squares
directions: Lightly grease a 10
x 15-inch pan.
Line bottom with 1 package of rolls.
(Flatten first with rolling pin.)
Beat together cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice. Spread cheese mixture over the bottom crust and cover with the 2nd package of rolls.
Beat egg white and brush over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: crispy cookies
directions: Mix all together in one bowl.
Drop by teaspoon and press flat with a flat bottom glass, dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325°
for 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: party peas
directions: Heat butter in large saucepan; add frozen peas.
Cover and cook slowly until peas are just defrosted.
Do not add water. When peas are thawed completely, add lettuce, onion and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Cover tightly and steam for 4 minutes, no more!
Yields 6 servings.

title: angie's chocolate pudding
directions: Stir cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Mix eggs and milk with whisk.
Add to cocoa mixture and stir while cooking.
Cook until thickens to light and fluffy mixture.
Pour directly onto vanilla wafers.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine yogurt and curry powder in a small bowl.
Makes 1 cup.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs, bananas, oats and nuts.
Beat until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Then sift 4 cups of self-rising flour and gradually add flour to mixture. Flour your wax paper, then flour dough.
Roll out, then cut out cookies.
Then place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.

title: baked fish with cheese sauce
directions: Make sauce of butter, flour, mustard, milk, salt and pepper, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until blended.
Pour over uncooked fillets in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange butter
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve at room temperature with bread or rolls.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Slice carrots thin.
Melt butter and remaining ingredients, cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Keep 1 cup broth aside.
Tear chicken into small pieces on bottom of casserole dish.
Heat milk, soup and butter until butter melts and mixture is well blended. Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Add Stove Top stuffing plus 1 cup chicken broth to top of casserole.
You do not need to prepare stuffing before adding to chicken.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: busy day chicken bake
directions: Bake chicken until done.
(To shorten this step, I use frozen diced chicken from Schwann or Sam's.)
Cool and tear into small pieces.
Lightly coat casserole dish with vegetable oil spray. Put chicken in bottom of casserole.
Layer Swiss cheese on top of chicken.
Mix soup and water together and pour over cheese.

title: ranger cookie
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Sift cinnamon and flour.
Add gradually, alternating with buttermilk.
Add nuts and raisins.
Fold in prune pulp.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours at 300°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble the muffins into a bowl.
Add the peas, Mexicorn, eggs, pepper, onion, mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste. Toss lightly.
Refrigerate and serve cold. Yield: 8 servings.

title: split pea soup
directions: In a stockpot, combine peas, ham, onion, bouillon, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Add carrots and celery and simmer 30 more minutes. Stir margarine into soup and heat through.
Serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salmon mini quiche
directions: Make enough pastry for 9-inch double pie; roll out pastry and cut into twelve 5-inch circles.
Set each circle loosely into large 3-inch muffin cups.
Chill; toss together Swiss cheese, salmon, onion, celery, parsley, flour and salt.
Spoon into shells; combine eggs and cream and pour over cheese mixture in shells.
Sprinkle each with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a long greased baking dish, place 1/2 of the dressing.
Put cut up chicken on top of dressing.
Mix soup and chicken broth saved from cooking chicken.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over chicken.
Place remainder of dressing on chicken; pour remainder of soup on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash, skin and cut up fryer.
Mix last 6 ingredients together in large bowl.
Heat enough oil in heavy, deep roasting pan so chicken will not be crowded while frying.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk.
Immediately roll in dry mixture and drop in very hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir blueberries in by hand. Grease top of muffin pan.
Use cupcake pans.
Put all the batter in 12 cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Brown Crisco and flour lightly. Add remaining ingredients, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil and season with salt and pepper.
If gravy is too thick, add more broth and bring to a boil.
Serve over chicken and dressing.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, onion, Parmesan cheese, eggs and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Press into pan and bake 30 minutes. Pour off drippings.

title: cheese souffl
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in next three ingredients.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese and heat until melted.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Beat egg yolks on high with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Stir into cheese mixture. Set aside.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar with electric mixer on high until stiff.
Fold egg whites into cheese mixture. Carefully pour into a well greased 1 quart souffl dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Serve immediately.

title: mom's dessert salad
directions: Combine hot water and jello.
Add bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Let set until solid.

title: lazy day stroganoff
directions: Put meat in crock-pot and add the other ingredients on top. Cook on low for 13 hours.
Add 8 ounces of sour cream and serve over rice or noodles.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the margarine and both sugars until light and
fluffy. Add oil and egg.
Mix well. Add oats, flour, corn flakes, nuts and coconut, if desired.
Mix well with salt, soda and vanilla.
Form into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: amy's cheese spread
directions: Stir cheese well to a spreading consistency.
Add eggs, pimentos, salt, pepper, sugar and enough mayonnaise to make a nice spreading mixture.

title: banana bread
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, salt and soda.
In
a second bowl, combine bananas and sugar; stir well.
Add egg and butter; stir to blend.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Mix until just moistened.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn onto rack.

title: easy peach dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dump in pan, the peaches, syrup and all.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cinnamon over cake mix.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cinnamon and sugar over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine and combine all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: pink pudding
directions: Make jello.
When almost set, beat evaporated milk and sugar until very stiff.
Beat jello; add to evaporated milk.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour jello mixture in pan. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils and boil in a saucepan with 4 cups of water for 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Place butter in a saucepan, add onions and saute about 3 minutes.
Add rice, carrot, beef, lentils, tomatoes, tomato paste and broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until all ingredients are cooked, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper and continue cooking for 3 minutes more.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Cut up.
Cut up fennel bulb and tops.

Cook in margarine with onion until tender. Stir in flour, then next 5 ingredients. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Stir in vegetables and seafood. Cook and stir 2 to 3 more minutes. Sprinkle with paprika (optional).

title: really easy corn fritters
directions: Pour 2 to 3 inches oil in heavy skillet and heat to 375°. Pour liquid from corn into medium bowl.
Add Bisquick and egg. Stir until smooth.
Fold in corn.
Batter will be thick.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Fry to gold brown.
Makes about 24 fritters.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: no salt spice mix
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
This is a real good way to keep salt off your table and out of your food.

title: broccoli and macaroni
directions: Brown garlic in olive oil.
Wash broccoli; cut it up.
Put in big pot filled with water.
When boiling, add in raw spaghetti and continue boiling about 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and pour garlic and oil over spaghetti.
Add black pepper and grated cheese. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond, mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown around edges.
Remove at once.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in 1/2 stick of margarine.
Mix ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper.
May need to add more milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta per instructions and when done, rinse under cold water.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Chill 2-3 hours before serving.

title: no bake chocolate cookie
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, cocoa, salt and milk in a large boiler for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats and vanilla.
When partly cooled, drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.
Make sure you get it all dropped before it gets cold.

title: sponge layer cake
directions: In small bowl of electric mixer, beat egg whites.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and cream of tartar; beat until stiff peaks form. Set aside.
In large bowl, beat egg yolks until light in color. Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and 2 teaspoons cold water; beat until frothy.
Gradually add hot water.
Slowly add sugar, then flour. Fold beaten egg whites into rest of batter.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans which have only the bottom greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool.
Frost with Cooked Icing (recipe given).

title: ginny's crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into patties.
Let chill in refrigerator.
Can be broiled or fried in Crisco.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening and eggs.
In another bowl, mix the cocoa with hot water to make paste, then add enough sour milk to make 2 cups of cocoa mixture.
Sift flour with soda; alternate milk and flour into creamed ingredients.
Add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits; roll in sugar and cinnamon mixed together. Put in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water together.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over biscuits, now nuts if used. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy cake(no mixer)
directions: Mix the butter and sugar with cake mix.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Fold in sour cream.
Spray Bundt or tube pan with Baker's Joy.
Sprinkle sugar in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into 4-quart freezer. Finish filling with milk.

title: escalloped potatoes and hamburger
directions: Mix together meat and salt.
Brown slowly in fat, stirring frequently.
Alternate in a buttered casserole layers of sliced potatoes, sliced onions and the browned meat.
Sprinkle each layer of potatoes with salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup and milk. Add green pepper; pour over mixture.
Cover; bake in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer, or until potatoes are tender.

title: banana split salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of juice.
Bring water to a boil; add gelatin and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool until partially set.
Toss bananas and lemon juice; fold bananas and pineapple into gelatin.
Pour into 9-inch dish; chill until firm.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg and pineapple juice.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter; cool.
Fold in whipped cream and spread over gelatin. Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: sharon's cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and dressing mix together. Refrigerate 1 hour. Mix ham into cheese mixture. Form a ball. Roll ball in nuts and parsley. That's it!

title: lime party salad
directions: Mix jello and water together.
Cool slightly.
Add other ingredients.
Use 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Place in bowl and sprinkle with salt; then toss.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid; do not rinse. Add green pepper, celery, onion and carrot.
Toss.

title: the best brussels sprouts
directions: Place the bacon in a large skillet over medium heat and cook until the fat is rendered.
Add the pine nuts and cook until the bacon is crisp and the nuts are golden, about 1 minute.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Rinse well and drain again.
Combine beans, onion and green pepper in a large bowl.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Add to bean mixture, tossing lightly to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: veggie linguine
directions: Cook linguine in a large pot of boiling water according to package directions. Drain and keep warm.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Heat oil to medium-hot and add garlic, zucchini, celery and onion to skillet. Stir-fry about 6 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with basil, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms and tomatoes and stir-fry 4 more minutes or until heated through. Toss with linguine.

title: alpine chicken bake
directions: Mix everything but bread cubes and Swiss cheese.
Place in casserole; top with bread cubes and Swiss cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar. Set aside. Mix vanilla pudding with milk and let set for 1 minute; combine with cream cheese mixture. Add teaspoon of vanilla and cool whip. Crush oreo cookies. Place some crushed cookies in bowl and add some mixture. Keep alternating until all mixture and cookies are used.

title: microwave french onion soup
directions: Combine onion and margarine in a microwave-safe dish covered with Saran Wrap and vented.
Cook on High 5 minutes or until onion is golden.
Dissolve broth mix in hot water and add to onions. Add pepper to taste.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese if desired.
Serve with French bread toast.
Makes 2 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil lemon rind with cloves and water for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and tea.
Stir in lemon and orange juice.
Serve hot. Serves 16.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour into a greased bundt pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes or until the top springs back and cake is golden brown.

title: wine-steamed clams
directions: Melt butter in 8-quart pan.
Add leeks and garlic; saute about 5 minutes until leeks are limp.
Add water, wine, thyme and pepper.
Cover and bring to boil over high heat.
Add clams, cover and cook until shells open, 8 to 10 minutes.
Discard unopened clams.
Ladle into bowls and offer lemon wedges.

title: banana split for adults
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan; add brown sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in bananas; coat well.
Add juices and liqueurs; simmer 2 minutes.
Serve immediately over ice cream.
Top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Place all of the ingredients into a double boiler and cook until thickened.
Stir frequently.
When mixture is thickened, pour into a 9-inch cooked and cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: cheddar fish bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fish.
Add fish and mix gently.
Place in a dish coated with nonstick spray.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
May be appetizer or entree.

title: meat and spaghetti casserole
directions: *If this is too much spaghetti, use what you like.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together and pour into greased and floured 8 in. pan. Bake at 350° for 25 min. Best when cool.

title: chichi dango(milk mochi)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Knead and wrap the dough in a wet cloth. Steam for 30 minutes or until mochi is translucent.
After steaming, put the mixture into a bowl and pound for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Place the dough in a pan or board that has been sprinkled with potato starch.
Cut into desired size.

title: ham and cheese bread
directions: Roll dough to 11 x 15-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with ham, broccoli and cheese.
Roll other loaf of dough and put on top. Seal edges and brush top with melted butter.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all together and form into balls.
Put on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Onion flakes may be substituted for the chopped onions.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and marshmallows.
Let set overnight.
Add pineapple, nuts, grapes and cream.
Fold in and let chill.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain juice from
fruit
and add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat
to
boiling, then add jello.
Stir in jello and marshmallows
and
simmer
until
marshmallows are melted. Add 1 cup cold
water
to
cool off. Break up cream cheese and add to jello mixture. Beat with mixture.
Jell a little either in refrigerator
or
freezer.	Fold in oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: old fashion boiled dinner
directions: Cover meat with cold water; heat rapidly to boiling, then remove scum.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender, 3 to 4 hours. Prepare vegetables, cutting turnips in quarters and cabbage into 8ths.
Cook beets in boiling water until tender.
About 45 minutes before serving, skim fat from liquid and add vegetables, except beets, and cook until vegetables are tender.
Drain; add beets. Serves 10.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a
13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and cut into bars. Yields 36 bars.

title: kate waller icing
directions: Melt and brown 1/2 cup sugar in small skillet.
Place 3 cups sugar and milk in large
boiler.
Bring
to
a
boil; add browned sugar, continue boiling until
this
makes a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour
in
mixing bowl with margarine.
Add vanilla and beat until
thick
enough
to spread on cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until well mixed.
Add syrup, sugar and lemon juice. Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and melted butter; mix.
Add pecans. Turn into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes longer or until set.

title: mock eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers. Cut to fit if needed. Make pudding with milk. Chill until set slightly. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour over crackers. Chill to set.

title: excellent soup dumplings
directions: Scald milk with butter added.
Remove from stove and stir in flour.
Mix well until it forms a ball.
Let it cool and add the following:
salt and eggs.
Beat very hard between each egg.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot soup and boil for 10 minutes.
Very good in chicken soup.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in double boiler top.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thick enough to mound slightly when dropped from spoon.
Cover; cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Stir a little hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, then stir all into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and 3/4 cup coconut.
Cool to room temperature. Turn into pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until stiff.
Put on top of pie.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken bake
directions: In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, arrange chicken skin side up. Drizzle on margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake until chicken loses its pink.
Serve on platter.
Stir sauce and spoon over chicken.
Garnish.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix buttermilk, instant pudding and container of Cool Whip. Add broken fudge stripe cookies last.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, salt and vanilla together.
Add flour and pecans to sugar mixture; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir all in a bowl and chill 12 to 18 hours.

title: mondel bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tin foil on 2 cookie sheets. Beat eggs well until thick.
Add sugar, oil, almond and vanilla extract and orange juice.
Beat well; add flour and baking powder to egg mixture one cup at a time, mixing well.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Divide dough by spooning onto cookie sheets 3-inches wide by 1-inch thick.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
Remove and cut into pieces.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Return to oven and bake 8 minutes until brown.
Turn over and repeat.
Cool and put in tight containers.

title: pork cutlets with mustard sauce
directions: Grill pork over medium-hot coals until done.
Do not overcook. May also fry.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and beat until light.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Spread into 2 greased and floured pans, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Spread thin.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: date pie
directions: Cut dates fine.
Pour milk over them and let stand a few hours or overnight.
Heat the date mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.
This was my Grandma Goshen's recipe.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Take off heat and mix sausage, rice, onions and celery in casserole.
If made ahead, refrigerate this portion and then when ready to bake, mix soy sauce, water and soup.
Pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Drop 1 tablespoon in hot oil at a time.

title: joann's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape mixture; put into loaf pan.
Cover top with 2 strips of bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: granny ruth's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over broccoli.
Make layers on top of broccoli with grated cheese, mashed up crackers and 1/4 pound melted margarine.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Brown onion in shortening; add beef. Grease a casserole dish and place half of noodles in dish. Put in half of meat and onions, then a layer of seasoning. Add 1/2 can peas and 1 can of the tomato soup. Repeat layer. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: lasagna(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients plus water.
Simmer covered for about 15 minutes. (During this time, cook noodles in boiling salted water.)
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients except Mozzarella.
Layer 1/2 the noodles in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Spread 1/2 the cottage cheese/egg mixture over noodles.
Layer with 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese, then 1/2 the meat mixture.
Repeat with other half of the noodles, cottage cheese/egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together; refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Add sugar, canned milk and oleo in a large pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring the mixture to a hard boil and then continue to cook it for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips (more chips can be added if you desire), then add marshmallow cream.
Beat for approximately 5 minutes and add nuts.
Pour out onto a large greased meat platter or cookie sheet.
Let the candy set and then cut in square pieces.

title: jerusalem chicken
directions: Toss all ingredients and chill.

title: mother's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Parkay oleo, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flavorings; beat well.
Add 3 cups flour and mix well.
Put cake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 350° for 70 minutes.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots until crisp-tender.
Layer the next three ingredients.
Combine soup, oil, sugar and spices.
Pour over. Refrigerate overnight.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water for 2 hours.
Heat fat in pot and saute onion, garlic and green pepper.
Add beans, ham bone and salt pork to boiling water and simmer slowly for 3 to 4 hours or until done. Season to taste and add parsley.
Serve with hot rice.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cook beef and onions and drain.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.
Stir baking mix and water until moist.
Spread evenly.
Spread beef mixture over batter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, melted butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare chicken breasts.
May wish to salt and pepper.
Roll the chicken breasts in the sour cream or yogurt.
Roll the chicken breasts next in the bread crumb mixture. Place in foil pan; cover with sliced mushrooms.
Dot tops with lo-cal butter (may wish to use less than the whole stick).
Bake for 1 hour, covered.

title: cheese fettuccine with peas and ham
directions: In a large pot, bring 5-quarts salted water to a boil.
In a frying pan, melt the butter over low heat.

Add the onion and saute, stirring frequently, until translucent, about 3 minutes. Add the cream, Camembert, Blue cheese, Swiss and Parmesan until the cheeses have almost completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Add the ham.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well and keep warm.

title: veggie weggies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Finely chop all your favorite vegetables.
Lay crescent rolls flat on pan and bake as directed. Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley mix.
After rolls are cool, spread the cream cheese mixture over this, then sprinkle on your chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle with grated Colby and Monterey Jack cheese.
Cover and chill before serving (overnight is best).

title: green chile cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to make a spreading consistency.
It's best served at room temperature, even better the next day.
Use crackers or bagels.
Yields 3 cups.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick well.
Form into balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
These may be frozen and baked as needed.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Mix melted margarine with melted chocolate chips.
Cool.
Then add beaten eggs.
Mix in rest of ingredients until well blended. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes in cupcake pans.
Makes 24.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into 2 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Turn once while baking.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add to dry mixture and stir well.
Store in refrigerator in Tupperware.
Bake as needed, 1 dozen or 1/2 dozen at a time.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This mixture keeps well and is so handy for hot muffins in a hurry.

title: double delight bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust.
Cover with top crust, crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 min.
Cool 10 min. before serving.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in onions, spinach, water chestnuts and red pepper.
Cover and refrigerate until flavor blends.
Serve with vegetables or assorted crackers.

title: luau
directions: Mix crumbled up corned beef and sauce (coconut milk); tear up some square pieces of foil wrap.
Arrange spinach leaves in foil, then pour sauce in it, not too much.
Watch overspills.
Then wrap tight and cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together. Cover and keep in refrigerator.
Make out as you wish and bake at 450°.
Keeps in refrigerator at least a week.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in medium saucepan.
Cover with water; bring to a boil.
Boil the potatoes until just tender when pierced with small sharp knife.
Cool.
Peel potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Prepare barbecue at medium-high heat or preheat broiler.
Brush potatoes with oil.
Sprinkle with rosemary, salt and pepper.
Grill potatoes until beginning to turn brown or about 4 minutes on each side.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into small balls.
Roll in cornstarch.
Brown slowly in oil for 20 minutes on low heat.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Make Sauce.

title: scripture cake
directions: Now follow Solomon's advice for making good boys, which means, beat well (Proverbs 23:14).
Stir together and bake in moderate oven at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: chili burger balls
directions: Mix meat mixture with egg, bread crumbs, milk, salt and paprika until well blended.
Shape into 16 balls.
Brown in oil; remove from pan and pour off drippings.
Stir chili sauce, water, brown sugar and mustard into kettle.
Return meat balls; cover. Simmer, stirring several times, 30 minutes or until meat balls are cooked through.
Serve with mashed potatoes or hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: autumn soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook and stir ground beef until brown. Drain off fat.
Cook and stir onions with meat until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tomatoes; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cover and simmer 10 minutes more, until vegetables are tender.

title: zucchini stir-fry
directions: Heat electric wok or skillet at 325° for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add oil and heat for 2 minutes.
Add celery, green pepper and onion. Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add zucchini and stir-fry 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
Serve immediately. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a 9-inch flowerpot and a shovel.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool and remove skin and bones.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soups and add to top of chicken.
Place stuffing on top of chicken soup mixture.
Add chicken stock on top of stuffing.
Bake at 350° until top is golden.

title: funny pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and melt butter in square cake pan.
Set aside.
In bowl, mix the sugar, cocoa, flour, vanilla, eggs and nuts.
Add butter to the mix.
Put batter in the buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients together, except meat.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; add meat and simmer 1 hour.
Serve on warm buns with coleslaw.
Pull the pork into pieces.

title: savory chicken bites
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend well. Stir in chicken, celery and pimiento.
Set aside.

title: eggs for brunch
directions: Butter a 2-quart round dish.
Place cheese on bottom; dot with butter.
Layer ham and tomato bits.
Mix eggs, cream, dill, salt and pepper.
Pour over all.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Mix well together and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut and ribs
directions: Layer separated ribs on top of sauerkraut in baking pan.
Bake at 375° until ribs are tender.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned but still soft.
(These cookies will puff up at first, then flatten out.)
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown beef.
Add jar spaghetti sauce and simmer about 10 minutes.
You may add additional seasonings such as garlic, green peppers, etc., to suit your taste.

title: easy chocolate moist cake
directions: Place chocolate and margarine in bowl.
Add boiling water. Stir until chocolate melts.
Add sugar.
With electric mixer on medium speed, alternate, mixing in flour and salt together and sour milk and soda together. Add vanilla extract in last part of milk mixture.
Drop in unbeaten egg and beat well.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° in 8-inch greased square pan 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 9 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cool under cold water.
Mix everything together.
Put into refrigerator for at least 3 to 4 hours to settle.
Enjoy!

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: snappy chicken balls
directions: Combine chicken, almonds, green onions and chutney.
In a separate bowl, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and curry powder. Combine chicken mixture and cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Shape in bite-size balls.
Roll each ball in grated coconut. Refrigerate covered until ready to serve.
Garnish with tiny yellow and white flowers or candied orange peel.
Makes 80 to 90 balls.

title: creamette summer salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions for salad use.
Drain.
Add tuna and next 6 ingredients.
Blend Italian dressing, sour cream and seasoned salt thoroughly.
Add to salad and toss well.
Chill.
Garnish with additional slices of cheese, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sesame pea pods
directions: Heat oil in 10 inch skillet over medium high heat. Add pea pods and sesame seeds. Cook about 2 minutes, stirring until pea pods are crisp tender. Stir in bell pepper. Cook about 2 minutes, stirring, until bell pepper is crisp tender.

title: chicken baked in rice
directions: Season
chicken
with
salt
and pepper.
Combine rice, soup mix, salt and water in baking dish.
Arrange chicken over rice. Dot
with
margarine;
cover.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: soy chicken
directions: Pour mixed ingredients over chicken pieces. Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: tomato and pear chutney
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pimiento.
Boil slowly for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add pimiento and boil 5 minutes longer. Pack into sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Add to rice.
Stir in cheese, soup and onions.
Pour into casserole dish. Cook approximately 30 minutes or until cheese appears to be thoroughly melted.
Do not overcook as casserole will be dry.

title: cheese straws
directions: Allow oleo and cheese to soften at room temperature.
Mix in rest of ingredients with electric mixer.
Make strips with a cookie press on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle red pepper on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen cabbage slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out juice and add carrot, peppers and celery (grated).

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and chocolate chips.
Melt chips and add to mixture.
Blend well and add in nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 12 pan at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients except coconut in blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Grease plate with Crisco.
Pour filling into plate and let set 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top and put in 350° or 400° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Dissolve cornstarch and mustard in vinegar.
Add ketchup, sugar, onion salt, celery salt, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent.

title: drumstick treat
directions: Mix wafers, 2/3 cup peanuts, butter and pat into bottom of 9x13 inch dish.

title: confectioners sugar from scratch
directions: Blend in blender until powdery.
Yields 1 1/2 cups (scant).

title: icebox fruit cake roll
directions: Thoroughly crush wafers.
Mix raisins, nuts and cherries.
Add to wafers.
Add milk.
Put mixture in refrigerator until chilled. Shape into desired size rolls.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on wax paper.
Wrap tightly around cake rolls.
Refrigerate.
(Will keep in refrigerator a month to six weeks.)

title: creamy party salad
directions: Drain pineapple well; save juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
Heat liquid to boiling.
Add boiling liquid to Jell-O to dissolve.
Add cream cheese while still hot and beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Let set in refrigerator until partially jelled.
When set, beat with rotary beater.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Dot with cherries after pouring into 9 x 12-inch pan.
You may sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Add the crushed pineapple, butter and salt to the mashed sweet potatoes.
Form into balls.
Place a marshmallow in the center of each one.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Place on baking dish; bake in a hot oven until lightly browned.

title: pineapple frostea
directions: Dissolve instant tea powder in ice water; stir in frozen juice concentrate until dissolved.
Pour pineapple-tea mixture into 6 glasses; add a scoop of pineapple sherbet to each glass.
Stir gently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: veggie meat loaf(diabetics)
directions: Place carrots, celery and onion in the container of a food processor or blender.
Process with on/off action until finely chopped (or shred by hand).
Combine vegetables and 1/2 cup of broth in frypan.
Stir-cook over medium heat 7 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Combine in a mixing bowl the remaining broth with the bread crumbs, parsley, egg, salt and pepper; add braised vegetables and ground beef.
Mix thoroughly. Form into a firm loaf, 2-inches thick.
Place in a shallow baking dish large enough for juices to drain away from meat loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes, until meat is no longer pink. Remove from oven and immediately place meat loaf on a warm serving platter so fat will not be absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.
Each serving:
1 slice, 1 1/2-inches thick, 147 calories, 2 protein choices, 1/2 fruit and vegetable choice.

title: zeeks sausage
directions: Break up Italian sausage and brown.
Add a little parsley, onion and garlic.
Saute.
Add tomato paste and whole tomatoes and mushrooms.
Simmer until it thickens (add water, if needed).
Mix Ricotta cheese with eggs, a little parsley, garlic, Parmesan and grated cheese.
Cook noodles; drain.
Layer in baking dish, starting with sauce, noodles and cheese mixture.
End up with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread. Add peanuts and cook until light brown in color. Remove from fire and fold in butter, soda, vanilla and salt. Quickly pour into buttered pan. Spread thin and allow to harden.

title: tuna sandwich spread
directions: Flake tuna with fork in medium bowl.
Add vegetables.
Combine yogurt, honey, lemon juice and mustard; mix with tuna and vegetables until evenly distributed and well moistened.

title: pineapple cucumber salsa
directions: In a large bowl, mix together well the pineapple, cucumbers, fresh mint, chili pepper, brown sugar, ginger root and lime juice. Cover and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: soy chicken
directions: Combine ingredients; add chicken.
Simmer on low until tender. Turn up heat to medium and cook until mixture turns to crust on chicken.

title: hearty cheese dip
directions: Cook meats in a skillet, crumbling as cooking, until well done.
Drain well in a colander.
Melt cheese and soups together in a crock-pot.
Add cooked well drained meats.
Keep warm to serve.
Serve as a dip or over mounds of corn chips, broken tortillas or whatever you desire.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix oleo and flour; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable waltz
directions: Bring vegetables to boil in salted water.
Cook 10 minutes, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with buttered cheese Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: impossible mexican pie
directions: Fry ground beef and drain grease.
Mix with taco seasoning. In glass pie dish, layer ground beef, onion, green chilies and Jack cheese.
In blender, mix milk, Bisquick, eggs and hot sauce. Pour over layered mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Let pie cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: microwave indoor s'mores
directions: Place 5 cups of miniature marshmallows, the corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips in large microwavable bowl. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring after each minute, until mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large bowl.
Mix quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Stir in 1 cup of marshmallows.
Make squares by pressing mixture evenly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand at least 1 hour, or refrigerate if a firmer bar is desired. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: granny's chocolate cake from scratch
directions: Bring water, cocoa,
oil and margarine to a boil.
Sift flour, sugar and salt into bowl.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Add
eggs,
buttermilk,
soda
and
vanilla. Cook in greased pan at 400° for 20 minutes, no longer.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add 2 large ripe mashed bananas and soda.
Add nuts if desired.
Spray Pan in loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: good chicken wings
directions: Cut off tip of chicken wing, then split in half.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine honey, ketchup, soy sauce, oil and garlic cloves.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Set oven for very hot (450°).
Grease 8-inch round cake pan. Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening with 2 knives or a pastry blender, until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Combine egg and milk; stir into flour mixture. If dough is too stiff, add more milk.
Pat or roll out into an 8-inch circle and put in pan.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Wash hands.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and put in square cake pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and peanut butter or butterscotch chips.
Add chocolate chips.
Add Eagle Brand milk and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prickly pear jelly
directions: Pick fruit of the Prickly
Pear
when
it is red, singe thorns off over fire.
Pick
enough
Tunas
to make at least 6 cups when chopped.
Cover
bottom
of dishpan with water.
Add Tunas and bring to a boil, mashing as they heat.
Strain (this should produce 4 cups
of liquid juice).
Combine the ingredients (except pectin) and heat
until
juice
climbs up side of dish pan about 3 inches.
Add
liquid pectin, bring to rolling boil	again for 1 minute.
Place
in	jars
and
seal.
Yields approximately 4 pints.

title: barbecued stuffed shrimp
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onions, celery and green pepper, using medium heat.
Stir in flour and milk, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add bread crumbs, crab meat, Worcestershire sauce, chopped parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Remove shells and veins from shrimp, leaving tails on.
Slit backs of shrimp.
Put two shrimp together with crab stuffing.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to cook.
Place shrimp in broiler pan, 5 inches from broiler unit.
Baste occasionally with sauce until shrimp are done, about 5 minutes on each side.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate chips) very well. Spread in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Cover with melted chocolate chips. Cut in squares.

title: no-bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: Microwave chocolate chips until melted.
Set aside to cool. Beat cream cheese, sugar and butter on medium speed of mixer until creamy.
Gradually add melted chocolate, beating on low until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: layered mushrooms and eggs
directions: In a pan over medium heat, stir soup and sherry until hot and smooth.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In a small bowl, toss cheeses lightly to mix; set aside.
Beat together eggs, milk, parsley, dill weed and pepper; set aside.

title: mud cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa to a full, rolling boil. Turn heat down very low.
Add peanut butter.
Turn heat off and add oats and vanilla.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Let it cool for a while, then cut.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel eggs.
Bring all seasonings to a boil in saucepan over high heat.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over eggs. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Keeps for several weeks if kept in refrigerator.

title: ann's burnt cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Lay graham crackers on pan. Boil brown sugar with margarine for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels and butterscotch morsels.
Spread over all.
Put in refrigerator for 3 minutes.
Take out and score.
Return to refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Take out and cut in squares.

title: wonder cake
directions: Mix together except shortening; add last. Bake at 350°.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: In a 4-quart crock-pot, stir together the potatoes and onion. Stir in the bacon. In large mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and pepper. Add the mixture to crock-pot. Cover and cook the soup on low heat for 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 to 5 hours. If you like, mash the potatoes for a slightly thicker consistency before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: mrs. bush's real chocolate chip cookie recipe
directions: Blend butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Sift and add flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans in slow oven, 300°, for 1 hour.

title: apple bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat applesauce slightly.
Add oleo, salt and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add yeast mix and half the flour.
Continue adding flour until a soft dough is formed. Knead on a floured board 8 to 10 minutes.
Grease dough lightly and put in a warmed, greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down in bowl and let stand 30 minutes.
Turn out onto floured board.
Cut into 2 equal pieces and let stand 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves and put on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: butterscotch balls
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients. Melt the margarine in shallow pan on low heat. Mix and roll balls. Melt the wax with the butterscotch chips. Dip balls and lay on wax paper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Blend flour in milk. Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks and seasonings.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Put crabmeat (or a mixture of crabmeat and shrimp) in mixing bowl and pour cooked sauce over it. Pour into a baking dish (8-inch square or 9-inch round Pyrex) and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: erwtensoep (dutch pea soup)
directions: Soak both types of peas overnight in just enough water to cover.
Next day, drain the peas, then place them in the 10 cups of water in a large pot with all of the other ingredients, except the sausage.
Bring to a boil, turn down heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
If soup becomes too thick, thin by gradually adding small amounts of water.
Remove ham hock.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add smoked sausage and continue simmering for 15 minutes.

title: swedish christmas punch(julglogg)
directions: Combine Aquavit, wine, sugar, spices and orange peel in saucepan.
Heat but do not boil.
Light with a match and pour burning into glogg glasses or heatproof cups containing a few almonds and raisins.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Wash and drain artichokes.
Rap artichokes (top) against countertop to open leaves.
Mix cheese, onions, garlic and bread crumbs.
Season to taste. Mix well. Stuff between leaves.
Place in a heavy gauge pot.
Add 1 cup water.
Pour oil over artichokes. Place in water.
Cook, covered, until one leaf can be pulled off. Serve hot.

title: hjortetakk
directions: Beat sugar and egg well.
Melt butter and cool.
Add sifted flour and hjortonsalt and add to mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Roll dough in long sticks the thickness of your finger.
Cut and make circles with the ends crossing each other.
Fry as doughnuts.

title: potato and rice soup
directions: Saute garlic in oil until brown.
Add onion, potato, rice, water and parsley; stir.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 people.

title: cocoa mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine nonfat dry milk powder, powdered sugar, unsweetened cocoa powder and nondairy creamer.
Stir until thoroughly combined.
Store cocoa mixture in an airtight container. Makes enough for about 45 (8 ounce) servings.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange the fryer in a shallow baking dish with skin side up.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours, basting every 15 minutes until chicken is tender and nicely browned.

title: rocky roads
directions: Cook for 1 minute the first 4 ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Add vanilla and marshmallows.
Drop on wax paper and chill.

title: crab supremes(makes 16 to 18 canapes)
directions: Drain crab meat.
Place in a 1-quart bowl and flake with a fork.
Add celery, mustard, pickle relish and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on crackers or toast rounds.
Place 8 at a time on a plate lined with a paper towel.
Cook on High for 30 seconds to 1 minute or until piping hot.

title: 3 fruit punch
directions: Mix juices together.
Add ginger ale and 7-Up.
Pour over sherbet.
(Do not add water to orange juice or lemonade.)

title: chicken rosemary
directions: Prepare chicken for frying.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix soft cream cheese (room temperature) and sour cream until real smooth.
Add the taco mix. Mix thoroughly and let set several hours or overnight.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot.
Cook on low heat, constantly stirring.
When it starts to thicken into a ball, put on counter and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: stuffing
directions: Put saffron in 1/4 cup of hot water.
Let stand a short while and then add 1 cup of milk.
Combine saffron and milk with eggs, salt and pepper and beat a little.
Put bread and onion in a large bowl.
Add milk mixture to bread and onion slowly.
Stir bread mixture thoroughly as you slowly add more milk.
If mixture is too dry, add a little more milk and stir.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in a large pan.
Pour the bread mixture into the pan; keep the heat low.
Turn bread mixture to other side to brown a little.
If too dry, add a little more butter to prevent sticking.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Crush bouillon cubes.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion. Cream in Philadelphia cream cheese.
Add Hellmann's mayonnaise and beat until well blended.
Chill.

title: cherry freeze
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: chicken pie(working family recipe)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and place in a large greased baking dish.
Place pie crust on top.
Bake at 400° until crust is brown.

title: macaroni salad(0 g. fat)
directions: Toss all of the ingredients lightly, add enough fat-free mayonnaise to desired moistness.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
If you want to cut out cookies, you must leave dough in refrigerator overnight so it will be more solid.
If not, make in balls the size of walnuts and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: "empanada" - spanish meat pie(family size)
directions: In deep skillet, saute sausage and bacon until cooked on low heat.
(Do not burn or crisp bacon.)
With slotted spoon, transfer meat to large mixing bowl, saving juice and oil from meat.
In same skillet, put peppers, onion, mushrooms, olives and tomatoes. Cook on low until peppers and onion are soft.
Transfer to mixing bowl with slotted spoon.
Add black pepper, salt, Parmesan cheese and eggs; mix well.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix 4 cups of water to jello.
Drain pineapple and oranges and add to jello when cool.
Add grated carrots. Serve with cottage cheese on a leaf of lettuce.

title: venison dip
directions: Saute onion; brown venison.
Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers; cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together, except the pudding.
Mix the pudding.
Put 1 layer of cake in punch bowl.
Put half of pudding and half of fruit mix. Put other layer of cake; repeat with pudding and fruit.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Layer cut strawberries on top.

title: chicken over rice
directions: Mix water, wine, soup and soup mix together with rice.
Put into casserole and season chicken.
Dip chicken into 1/4 pound melted butter or margarine.
Lay on top of rice.
Add paprika. Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, in a 350° oven.
Uncover for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cut cookie dough roll into halves lengthwise. Cut each half into slices.
Arrange half the slices in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and cream cheese in bowl until smooth.
Spoon over cookie dough.
Top with remaining cookie dough; slices will not overlap.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: chocolate-cherry cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well by hand.
Stir in cherry pie filling, chocolate chips and nuts.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in large bowl.
About 1/2 hour before serving, mix dressing mixture with salad.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix soda in applesauce and add to sugar mixture.
Sift spices with flour, adding raisins and nuts to batter before the flour.
Bake in moderate oven and frost with Caramel Frosting:

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine together.
Add eggs, then flavoring and milk, alternately with flour.
Start in cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lazy man's cabbage rolls
directions: Brown hamburger with onion soup.
Add tomato soup, water and rice.
Chop cabbage into bottom of casserole.
Place hamburger mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: honey garlic loin
directions: Marinate 4 to 24 hours.
Grill until done.

title: grannie's sweet pickles
directions: Add to cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
Boil for 35 minutes and put in jars.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Saute thin sliced zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
Combine eggs and cheese and stir into zucchini mixture.
Separate dough into 8 triangles and press into 10-inch quiche pan.
Press over bottom and up sides.
Spread mustard over crust and pour in the vegetable mixture.

title: caramel turtles
directions: Place pecan halves in groups of 4's on greased cookie sheet. Place on top of each group a caramel.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes. Cool.
Top with melted chocolate.

title: theresa's cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl; cut in Crisco with pastry blender.
Stir in milk and egg.
Do not overmix.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except mayonnaise) together.
Add mayonnaise to taste.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in bottom of baking dish.
Slice onions over the potatoes.
Season with garlic salt.
Spread with 1 can of cream of mushroom soup.
Flour and brown chops in skillet.
Lay on top of sliced potatoes in dish.
Take another can of cream of mushroom soup; add 1/2 to 1 can of milk to make gravy.
Pour over chops and potatoes.
Cover and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: vanilla butter nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add one egg at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk to creamy mixture.
Fold in flavoring.
Pour into floured and greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: chilli beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add all ingredients and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli rice cheese casserole
directions: Saute the celery and onions in the margarine.
Mix with the rice and the broccoli.
Add the celery.
Add the soup and the Cheez Whiz, mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lo-fat beef stew
directions: Spray roaster with cooking spray or use 1 tablespoon canola oil.
On medium-high brown lean beef, stirring slowly to keep from scorching.
When meat is browned, add salt, pepper, garlic and about 1 quart water.
Cook on medium until meat is tender (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Add fresh carrots and cook 1/2 hour more; then add potatoes and tomatoes to sauce.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Serve with baked cornbread and fresh tossed salad. Good!

title: hot caramel dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients other than apples or pound cake in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into crock-pot.
Set on low.
Dip fresh apple slices or cake cubes into hot caramel.

title: broiled marinated chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with garlic, basil, thyme and pepper.
Arrange chicken in shallow bowl.
Mix together vinegar and orange juice; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Place chicken on broiler pan.
Set temperature control at broil, 500°.
Arrange oven rack so chicken is about 4 inches from heat.
Broil, turning, about 6 minutes per side, or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve with wild rice, pouring pan drippings over rice. Makes 2 servings.

title: oyster nachos
directions: Drain oysters or shuck fresh ones.
Pour rock salt in an ovenproof pan.
Position shells in rock salt to steady the shells and insulate the nachos.
Place a few chip pieces in each shell, then an oyster on top.
Add a dollop of red sauce and some grated cheese.
Broil until the cheese melts and the edge of oysters curl. Top each nacho with jalapeno slice.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Mix sugar and 4 cups warm water and bring to a boil. Add jello mix and all juices and mix well. Freeze. Take out of freezer 4 hours before using. Add ginger ale. Makes about 24 cups.

title: bisquick mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add Crisco and blend by hand or pastry blender
until
mixture looks like cornmeal.
Store
in glass, plastic
or
can
container
with tight-fitting lid.

title: "pigs in the blanket" stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cabbage).
Parboil cabbage to loosen leaves.
Trim core.
Separate leaves.
Roll meat mixture into a leaf, not too tightly.
Place in frypan or pot.
Cover with tomato soup.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.

title: very easy homemade rolls
directions: Put Crisco, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Over this mixture, pour 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until shortening is about dissolved.
Add eggs and stir together well.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in warm water.
Stir in flour, unsifted.
Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on floured pastry sheet or waxed paper and cut with 2-inch cutter.
Put in a greased pan and let rise until double in size (about 3 to 4 hours).
If room is cool, turn oven on to warm slightly.
Turn off and let rolls rise in oven.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Brush tops with melted oleo, if desired, before baking.
Makes about 4 dozen rolls and doesn't even require kneading.
My teenage granddaughters make these since they are so easy!

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until fluffy.
Add pecans and mix until all nuts are coated.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add nuts; coat thoroughly.
Place on buttered pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: frozen cabbage slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage and let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Mix all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Cool and freeze in plastic containers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie crust and cool.
Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle 3/4 of mixture on bottom of pie crust.
Pour vanilla pudding over mixture. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture on top. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Toss Croutettes stuffing mix with melted margarine. Set aside for topping.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; beat as directed on cake mix.
Add frosting to batter.
Bake in angel food pan in 350° oven for about 55 minutes (grease and flour pan).

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in refried beans, taco sauce, taco seasoning and green chilies.
Layer half of the tortillas on bottom of baking dish.
Spread half the meat mixture. Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat gradually.
Beat in well beaten eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Beat in salad dressing.
Toss together remaining ingredients.
Pour on dressing; toss gently.
Serves 6.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and save broth to use as needed. Cut chicken into cubes. Mix all ingredients. Place in a casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt oleo and add graham crackers, sugar and peanut butter. Press into a buttered 9 x 13 inch pan. Melt chips and spread over bars. Cut into squares before chocolate is too firm. Keep refrigerated.

title: della joseph's "hanging on a chip"
directions: Brown sausage and ground meat; add onion at the last so it just wilts.
Add cheese and soup; stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to serve hot.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in ice cream churn, filling with plain milk to fill line.

title: can't fail short pie crust
directions: In a 9-inch Pyrex pie plate, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and sugar and blend.
Then add cooking oil and milk and blend good. Press mixture on sides and bottom of pie pan.
Prick crust.
Flute edge.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: lentil minestrone soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium-high heat, cook onion and garlic in hot oil about 5 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently.
Add carrot, celery, lentils, spinach, water, bouillon granules, oregano and thyme.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and pasta; simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer or until pasta is just tender.

title: sourdough donuts
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let rise until double; knead down.
Roll out.
Cut and let rise until light.
Fry in deep fryer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 16.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix together coleslaw mix and mayonnaise. Then toss the rest together.

title: chocolate peanut butter toffee
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Place saltine crackers end to end on foil.
In saucepan, melt butter and sugar.
Bring to boil for no longer than 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.

title: peach cake(from grandma jennie shull)
directions: Arrange sliced peaches on bottom of 13 x 9 cake pan. Mix jello and cake mix and spread over peaches. Make holes in mixture and pour over the margarine (melted). Pour water and peach juice over all. Bake at 400° for approximately one hour.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Melt
the
chocolate chips and almond bark in microwave for approximately 3 1/2 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir.
Turn out
on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.	Let dry and enjoy!
Yields 100 clusters.

title: sweet 'n' peanut buttery sandwiches
directions: Spread bread slices with soft butter.
Sprinkle one tablespoon brown sugar on one slice of bread.
Spread the other slice with peanut butter as thick as you please.
Slice across the center. Serve with milk.
If desired, toast the bread first.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook meat in water until tender and
you can easily pull apart.
Prepare sauce with remaining ingredients.
Let come to a boil and pour over meat.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, starting with chicken, then in order listed.
Put two pats of butter on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger until brown; drain.
Stir in sauce and soups and cook until hot and bubbly.
Crush 1/2 bag tortilla chips and place in bottom of rectangular dish.
Pour mixture on top and top with the rest of the bag of crushed chips and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a pan heat the milk, blend in the bread cubes.
In a large bowl combine the sugar, vanilla, salt, raisins and eggs. Blend the milk mixture into the egg mixture.
Pour it into a greased baking dish.
Place in a pan of hot water (sprinkle with nutmeg).

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch dish or pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cook and stir beef and onions over medium heat until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth; pour into plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce, if desired.

title: sour milk cake
directions: Bake at 350° in Bundt pan.
May be iced; also good without icing.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread the pineapple in a 12 x 9-inch pan (do not drain). Spread the pie filling over the pineapple.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the pie filling.
Sprinkle the nuts over the cake mix.
Put the margarine patties on top of the nuts.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole in crock-pot
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot and cook.
Stir often. Cook until done.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan the sauce, uncooked noodles, hamburger, cottage cheese mixture and grated Mozzarella cheese. Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered with foil.
Serves 6.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Prepare salmon by making sure there are no bones or anything in the salmon you may remove.
Add all ingredients together.
You can add chopped onion, if you desire.
Thoroughly mix and press the mixture into small, 3-inch wide patties.
Place in a large frying pan in oil just enough to cover the bottom of the pan well. Fry; turn as each side browns.
Remove.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook squash, celery and onion until tender on top of stove.
Add soup and cook in oven.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Baking time is 30 minutes.

title: baked vidalia
directions: Peel onion and cut.
Scoop out the top of onion large enough to hold butter.
Place butter in hole and sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream shortening, sugar and extracts. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Roll into little balls and roll in a bowl of 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add egg, milk and melted shortening. Mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin pans. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: good crisp sweet pickles
directions: Place pickles in
jars
and pour this cool mixture over the pickles.
Put in canner and cook until pickles turn color. May add dill, red pepper and garlic.

title: custard
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Let almost boil.
Add sugar gradually while stirring.
Beat eggs in blender and add some of the hot milk to eggs, then add egg mixture to hot milk.
Cook until custard coats the spoon.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly and add vanilla and salt.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp-tender; drain and place in casserole dish.
Spread soup over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over soup. Pour beaten eggs over cheese.
Mix margarine with crumbled crackers and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: caramel ring
directions: Melt sugar, nuts and butter.
Pour half into a tube or Bundt pan.
Arrange biscuits overlapping each.
Pour remaining mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce evenly in bottom of 8 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle celery on top of lettuce, then green pepper, onion and peas.
Mix mayonnaise with sour cream and spoon over vegetable mixture. Sprinkle sugar over sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle top with the cheese and bacon.
Cover tightly with foil, leaving air space between foil and salad.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Makes 9 servings.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Place in a shallow container. Add tenderloins, turning to coat.
Cover and chill 4 hours. Remove tenderloins from marinade.
Grill, covered, 6-inches from medium coals until done, turning once.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Baked in a wood stove oven.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in salad bowl.
Chill before serving.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix both pudding mixes, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour over graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers over this.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Boil pineapple with juice and lemon jello until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Fold together buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Add cooled pineapple mixture and blend well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 15.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients to mix.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: williamsburg chicken 'n ham bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
