Melt 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan; toss in bread crumbs.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, melt remaining butter.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Stir in flour and salt and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in cream and milk.
Add sage.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat and stir in ham and chicken.
Pour mixture into 8 to 9-inch pie pan or quiche dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake about 25 minutes or until mixture is bubbling and bread crumbs are brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potatoes, mash in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add flavoring and sugar until mixture is like dough.
Roll out on waxed paper.
Spread generously with peanut butter.
Roll into a log.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice.
Store in refrigerator.
Rolls may be frozen. Yields about 50 to 60 pieces.

title: gooey bars
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; place in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Combine the next 4 ingredients; mix well. Pour over cake batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Cook until thick and clear.
Cool completely.
Add 2 cans drained mandarin oranges and 1 (12 ounce) Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Sift remaining ingredients together; add to the wet mixture.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: helen's day before curried rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add next 5 ingredients; toss to mix.
Place in a 17 1/4 x 11 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch baking pan.
Drizzle chicken broth over evenly, mixing lightly with fork.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bubble solution recipe(craft idea)
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Let stand for several hours.
Scoop any suds off the top and start blowing!

title: banana punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except ginger ale) and run through blender.
Freeze mixture. To serve, mix partially thawed mixture with ginger ale.
Serves 75.

title: veg-all beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles or rice until tender.
Lightly brown onion in butter, add ground beef and cook slowly until brown.
Blend in flour.
Add cooked noodles, vegetables including liquid, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour in greased baking dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: italian sausage salad
directions: To Cook Sausage:
Prick skins, put in a skillet with water to cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute; drain.
Slice in 1/2-inch lengths and fry over medium heat until brown and cooked through.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, combine peanut butter, shortening, granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract.
Beat with electric mixer on medium until smooth and creamy.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Drop by 1 1/2 teaspoons on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten in a crisscross pattern with a fork dipped in sugar.
This is the trademark of peanut butter cookies, you know.
Bake cookies 8 to 10 minutes, until golden.

title: raisin pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, flour, milk, butter and raisins. Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Pour in a baked crust.
Beat egg whites, pour on pie and brown.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring water, butter and cocoa to a boil. Remove from heat and add flour, sugar and salt. Beat in eggs, sour cream and baking soda. Bake at 350° in a 15 1/2 x 12 1/2 x 1-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix, making 2 round pans or one 9 x 13-inch. Split layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend well and chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers of cake.
Combine reserved sour cream mix with Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal in tight container.
Refrigerate 3 days.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Put sweetened condensed milk and lemonade in large mixing bowl.
Stir until lemonade melts, then pour in Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Put pie shell in oven until golden brown, then put mixture in.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes; try with a toothpick.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup topping; press remaining in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Blend sugar with cream cheese; add egg, milk, lemon and vanilla.
Spread over crust and sprinkle with reserved mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with flour and sugar.
Add Karo.
Add pecans, vanilla and melted butter.	Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream together, then add the following things and beat with hand mixer.
Put in freezer and freeze.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Brown
meat.
Mix
all	other ingredients together with meat. Bake in a covered casserole dish at 375° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine pork and beans, mustard, ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Brown beef and drain; stir into bean mixture.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger. Add beef. Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in frying pan or wok. Add beef and toss over high heat until brown.
Mix cornstarch with water. Stir in pan until thick.
Add tomatoes.

title: banana bread pudding
directions: Place the bread cubes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour butter over and toss to coat.
In a medium bowl, lightly beat eggs, add milk, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in bananas.
Pour over bread cubes and stir to coat.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: red hot jello salad
directions: Bring water to boil. Add red hots, stirring until melted. Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer, partly covered, for 2 hours.
(Simmering can be done in a crock-pot.)
Can be frozen in separate containers for more than one meal.
When thawed, heat through and serve over spaghetti.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given. Place in greased 10-inch pie pan.
No crust is needed.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In 12 inch, non-stick skillet, heat oil over medium high heat and cook pepper 2 minutes.
Add chicken and cook 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Stir in soup mix blended with water. Simmer 2 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve in warm tortillas. Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pie shell according to directions for empty baked crust.
Cool.
Chop one cup of strawberries.
tags: Pet-Ritz deep dish pie crust shell

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and reserved liquid until blended.
Add some cocktail sauce for color (approximately 1 tablespoon).
Add crab; serve with cocktail sauce on the side (or shape into a bird's nest with sauce in the center). Place crackers on side.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Add frozen berries. Chill until starting to set.
Pour over cake, broken into pieces.
Mix in 9 ounces topping. Coat all cake.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan that has been sprayed with Pam no-stick.
Chill until firm.
Ice with 3 ounces topping and garnish with whole strawberries.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8-inch dish. Cut crusts from bread and cut each slice into 5 fingers. Place bread fingers over fruit. Mix sugar, flour, egg and butter. Pour over fruit and bread.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons on bottom of baking dish; top with cheese.
Add drained, scrambled sausage.
Mix eggs, mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk; pour over sausage.
Let set overnight in fridge.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Grease 1-quart casserole; put bread cubes in casserole.
In small pan, melt oleo with sugar; add eggs, flour, pineapple and juice.
Mix and pour over cubes; toss and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake covered at 350° for at least half an hour.
Great as a side dish with chicken, pork or ham.

title: potatoes by sarah
directions: Boil potatoes until done, but firm.
Slice crosswise.
Warm mushroom soup.
Layer ingredients and dot with margarine in a casserole dish, adding salt and pepper on each layer.
Having soup warm makes it spread a little easier.
Could add shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream
by
hand oleo, sugar, flour and Velveeta cheese. Put 1 can apples in bottom of casserole sprayed with Pam.
Top apples with
the
above mixture.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes.
(Very good!)

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in bananas, oats and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Mix sugar,
eggs,
flour
and baking powder; beat well. Heat butter and milk to boiling point and add last.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add unbeaten eggs.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt together.
Add to first mixture, then add milk and rind of lemon.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let cool about 5 minutes in pan. Mix 1/4 cup sugar with juice of 1 lemon (about 1/3 cup lemon juice) and pour over the top of bread.
When cool, remove from pan.

title: coconut cake
directions: Reserve egg whites for icing.

title: bride's dinner(pork chops)
directions: Combine bread cubes, egg, butter, seasonings and onion.
Shape into four balls.
Place chops in shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place one ball of stuffing on each chop. Core apples.
Set in pan with chops.
Combine raisins, sugar and cinnamon.
Fill centers of apples.
Roll sweet potatoes in melted butter.
Place in pan with chops and apples.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: yellow punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water (heating is best); stir in the juices and Kool Aid.
Freeze in containers that will be easy to remove the punch.
When ready to use, remove from freezer 30 to 45 minutes earlier.
Put punch in punch bowl; add ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: turkey or chicken pot pie
directions: Melt mayo in a heavy pan over low heat; add flour, stirring constantly until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in turkey, mixed vegetables, bouillon granules and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Spoon into a 9-inch pie plate.

Unroll crescent rolls and place side by side on lightly floured surface, firmly pressing perforation together to seal. Arrange over whole pie with slits cut into it or lattice design. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes and scoop out insides.
Set tomatoes and tops aside.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Shake well.
Pour over crunchy broccoli.
Marinate.
Run under cold water to make it crunchy.
Chopped eggs and parsley on top.

title: old-time bread pudding
directions: Put the buttered toast into a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish. Cut into squares.
Sprinkle the seedless raisins over the toast. Mix the eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, Pet milk, boiling water and vanilla; pour over toast.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then sprinkle with 4 teaspoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: herb seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Toss gently with spoon until well blended.
Store in an airtight container in a cool, dry, dark place for up to six months.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup butter and cracker crumbs.
Place in dish.
Slice bananas on crumbs.
Make sauce of eggs, sugar and 1 cup butter. Whip 15 minutes.
Spread over bananas and drain pineapple.
Pour over sauce.
Add whipped topping.
Add chopped cherries and nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add canned milk, then vanilla.
Pour into freezer.
Finish filling with milk.

title: biscuit and chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (save broth).
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in casserole dish.
Mix soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Put canned biscuits on top.
Bake until biscuits are brown.

title: strawberry yum-yum
directions: Blend together well the margarine and graham cracker crumbs. Cover bottom of 9 x 13 x 2 pan with half of mixture. Beat together the sugar, Dream Whip, cream cheese and milk. Spread over mixture. Cover with pie filling. Spread remaining cream mixture. Sprinkle crumbs over top. Chill for 12 hours before serving.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until dry.
Cool.
Then add applesauce, eggs, vegetable oil, liquid sweetener and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix in with other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pot roast and vegetables
directions: Brown roast in all sides in hot fat in pressure pan.
Season and add water.
Cover and cook roast at 15 pounds pressure for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let pressure return to normal.
Open cooker, place vegetables on top of roast.
Season.
Cover and cook at 15 pounds pressure for 10 minutes longer.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Mix meat, egg, bread crumbs, seasonings and half the soup mix. Shape into 4 patties and brown on both sides in oil.
Remove meat.
Blend flour into drippings.
Add mushrooms and liquid plus enough water to make 2 cups (or substitute some milk, about 1/2 cup).
Cook until thickened and smooth.
Add mushrooms and remaining onion soup mix.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add meat and heat through.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In bowl, beat sugar, butter, oil, milk, extract and egg until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Spread evenly in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with a cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cinnamon butter cake
directions: Blend together the cake mix, vanilla pudding (dry), oil, eggs, water and flavoring.
Beat 4 minutes.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and spiral this through batter.
Pour into tube or Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: clam dip
directions: In mixing bowl, combine clams and juice from can.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese and chopped onion.
Add to above.
Add lemon juice and vinegar and mix well.
Great dip with crackers or veggies.

title: cornbread for a crowd
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine oil, cornmeal, eggs, corn and sour cream; pour into greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then lower temperature to 375° and cook 30 minutes more. Serves 12.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium size, heavy bottomed saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add lemon juice, cold water and egg yolks; stir with whisk until smooth.
Stir in boiling water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture begins to boil. Cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add margarine and lemon peel and stir until melted and combined.
Remove from heat and set aside while making the meringue.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites to a peak, gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Place cookies in oven and immediately turn off oven.
Leave in closed oven overnight.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Mix milk, sugar and flour; pour over butter.
Add peaches on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare the stuffing as directed on box, but use broth from boiled chicken in place of water.
Pat or lay dressing in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan or use large Corning Ware dish.
Layer the deboned chicken over the dressing.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven in hot oil, brown roast.
Spoon off fat and add mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup of water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours.

title: chili beans
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper together, then add meat. Brown and drain. Add rest of ingredients.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook whole chicken in water, onion, parsley, salt, etc., until falls apart and broth is very rich and good.
Strain both.
Take chicken meat off bone; dice.
Cook thick egg noodles (Kluski type or homemade if you can get them) in simmering broth until done; add chicken meat and heat through.
Yummm!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage, then beat the eggs.
Add milk and grated cheese with the broken bread and combine in a baking dish.
Bake in the oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Parboil; drain.
Add to baking dish. Mix all ingredients and add to beans.
Add water to cover.
Bake at 250° for 6 to 8 hours.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix together margarine, Karo, salt and brown sugar in microwave-safe bowl.
Cook margarine, Karo, salt and brown sugar 5 minutes (on High) in microwave.
Stir once while cooking.
Add baking soda.
Mixture should bubble.
Pour popped corn into large brown paper bag.
Pour caramel mixture over corn.
Microwave 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave 1 minute more.
Stir.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: peanut squares
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat. Add marshmallow and stir until completely melted. Stir in peanut butter until melted. Remove from heat. Add cereal and stir until coated. Press mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: spicy sugared nuts
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place nuts in small bowl.
Pour egg white over nuts and stir until well coated and sticky.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over nuts, stirring until completely coated. Spread on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
May also dust with confectioners sugar after baking.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Slice squash in half inch pieces.
Boil 3 minutes or until tender.
Add onion, eggs and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into one quart casserole.
Mix butter and crumbs and sprinkle over squash. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes until brown.
Serves 6.

title: liver and onions
directions: Dip liver in flour.
Heat fat or oil in frypan.
Cook liver in the pan over medium heat until browned on one side.
Turn liver and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put onion on liver.
Add water.
Cover pan tightly and cook over low heat for about 20 minutes, until liver is tender.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into small chunks. Combine with remaining ingredients in bowl. No need to thaw peas first.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Combine milk, cereal and bananas.
Add egg and shortening. Beat.
Combine dry ingredients; add to banana mixture, stirring only until flour mixture is moistened.
Add flavoring and stir. Fill greased muffin pan two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Slightly beat egg whites and water with fork thoroughly.
Mix nuts in mixture.
Sprinkle spices and salt over nuts; mix all together.
Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 300° oven.
Pack in covered jar.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle uncooked rice evenly over bottom of rectangular baking dish.
Add water.
Combine soups, add milk and heat.
Pour mixture over rice.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Seal with two layers of aluminum foil.
Bake for 2 hours and 15 minutes at 325°.
Yields four large portions.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until set and serve.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Steam cauliflower until begins to get tender, yet still firm. Break apart flowerets and arrange in casserole.
Gently mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over flowerets.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash until done.
Beat well and let cool.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jean walsh's crumb cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on box.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 12 x 18-inch greased and floured pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix remaining ingredients and toss with dressing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and Karo.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour over pecans in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beans and polish sausage
directions: Slice Polish sausage 1-inch thick.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot or oven (375°) for 2 hours.

title: pineapple boat
directions: Cut pineapple lengthwise.
Scoop out pineapple.
Mix pineapple pieces with all of the remaining ingredients.
When ready to serve, return ingredients to pineapple halves.

title: *rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate pieces, chocolate and butter in a large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat. Beat eggs until foamy.
Mix in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Stir in peanuts and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm. Store in the refrigerator; remove just before serving.
Makes about 4 dozen candies.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain juice off salmon; save some to mix with mixture if it's too dry.
Make into patties; fry in a nonstick pan.
Makes 6 patties.

title: tasty cabbage(microwave)
directions: Put water in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add other ingredients. Cover dish and microwave approximately 8 minutes on High or until desired crispness is obtained.
Serves 6.

title: saucy green beans
directions: Boil green beans until done.
Meanwhile, cook bacon until crisp; chop.
In a large frying pan, saute onion in 2 tablespoons bacon grease until tender.
Add bacon, vinegar, sugar, bean water and beans to frying pan.
Warm through and serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix oleo, granulated sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Chill dough for several hours.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Then roll balls in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Cook all together for about 1 hour; put into jars and seal.

title: spanish coffee
directions: To sugar rims of glasses, dip lemon moistened rims into granulated sugar.
Put Kahlua and brandy into coffee glass.
Fill coffee to within 1/2 inch of rim.
Top with whipped cream to the brim.
Do not stir.
Serves 1.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll in foil (shiny side up).
Tap each end on hard surface to make firm.
Place in icebox for 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of foil before placing on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: original chex party mix
directions: In small bowl, add Lawry's and Worcestershire sauce to melted margarine or butter.
Mix well.
Pour Chex cereals, nuts and pretzels into large plastic bag.
Pour margarine or butter mixture over cereal in bag.
Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated. Pour contents into large microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for five to six minutes, stirring every two minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container.

title: beef roast
directions: Put roast in deep pan.
Pour can and dry soups over roast. Add mushrooms and water.
Cover and cook at 350° until done.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute celery, green pepper, onion and garlic in cooking spray for two to three minutes.
Add bulgur, bouillon, tomato juice, tomato paste, spices and soy sauce.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer on low for 20 minutes.
Add beans.
Cook gently until desired consistency.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
One gram of fat per serving.

title: easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Also good microwaved.

title: south jersey crumb cake
directions: Rub together first 3 ingredients with pastry blender.
Save out 1 cup of crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Then add raisins (and currants if desired).
Pour batter into a greased 9-inch diameter pan. Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat pan with oil.
Add chicken and brown.
Remove.
Add vegetables, garlic, salt and pepper and water.
Saute.
Add chicken and tomatoes; cook for 30 minutes.
Can be cooked in a wok.

title: chicken or tuna loaf
directions: Combine gelatin, cold stock or water and boiling stock.
Let cool.
Add lemon juice and mayonnaise.
As it thickens, add whipping cream, tuna or chicken, celery, olives, parsley, cottage cheese and salt.

title: big catch casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a pizza pan. Bake as directed.
Mix cream cheese and dressing and spread on cooled crescent rolls. Chop vegetables and put on pizza.
Refrigerate, cut and serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil; drizzle over vegetables and toss well.
Chill at least 24 hours before serving.

title: fresh peaches in champagne
directions: Prick whole peaches with fork.
Place peach in bottom of each champagne glass and fill with iced champagne.
Guests sip their champagne, then eat the juicy peach.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach 3 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Drain well. Add soup mix and mayonnaise.
Mix with mixer until well mixed.

title: korean fried rice
directions: Precook rice and refrigerate.
Cut ham into square cubes. Chop green onions.
Slightly preheat a large frying pan with oil over medium heat.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: royal scallop
directions: Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add ham, eggs and crackers. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Cut center out of bread and set aside.
Fill hole with mixture and put top of bread back on. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot!
When taking out of oven, remove top, chop and dip pieces.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan with spaghetti
directions: Flatten chicken to an even thickness, using palm of hand or meat mallet.
Dip chicken in egg; coat with bread crumbs.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken until browned on both sides.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses and parsley.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: whipped cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl. Blend in whipped cream with a fork until dough is stiff.

title: scalloped tuna and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, sliced, until soft in salt water.
Melt butter in top of double boiler over direct heat; stir in flour and mustard.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Stir over boiling water until smooth and thick.
Arrange potatoes, tuna and onion in alternate layers in greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: play dough for kids
directions: Cook all ingredients over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring vigorously until it forms a ball.
Remove dough from pan and let stand on counter for 5 minutes.

title: people chow
directions: First melt together margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Put Rice Chex in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over it.
Stir carefully but mix well.
Put powdered sugar in brown paper sack.
Add cereal mixture and shake well.
Pour out of bag and chill.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: amaretto apricot chews
directions: Stir together flour and baking soda.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add brown sugar and sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and 1 tablespoon Amaretto and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Stir in oats, apricots and almonds.

title: plantation dinner
directions: Cook meat and onions together until brown and tender.
Stir in cream cheese, milk and soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a large casserole dish and heat in oven for 20 minutes at 320°.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Boil and stir first 4 ingredients.
Add hot dogs.
This can be doubled, tripled, whatever your needs.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar until it is smooth.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and bananas.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour.
Chill dough for at least one hour.
Roll dough out on floured surface.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Ice.
Decorate, if desired.

title: won ton
directions: Cook all ingredients together.
Let cool, then put 1/2 teaspoon in won ton wrappers and deep fry.

title: ole' fashioned baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
In a Dutch oven, cook beans in 8 cups water until tender; add the other ingredients.
Cover with bacon.
Bake for 2 hours or more, if needed, in 350° oven.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; mix into pudding.
Blend can of worms inside mixture.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer sliced potatoes with onions, if desired, with cream of mushroom soup (2 cans if full crock-pot).
Season to taste.
Cook on high for three hours
Add cheese on top of potatoes and cook one more hour on high.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Drain pineapple well, pressing out juice with back of a spoon. Reserve 3/4 cup of juice.
Cover pineapple and refrigerate. Combine juice, pumpkin, sugar, eggs, spices and gelatin in saucepan.
Simmer on low heat 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Beat cream cheese and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually beat in warm pumpkin mixture until well blended.
Refrigerate overnight. Next day, fold pineapple and marshmallows into Cool Whip and spread over top of pumpkin.
Keep refrigerated.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Stir salt, baking powder and flour together and work in shortening (butter); add egg yolk to mixture and fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Spread mixture 1/2-inch thick in shallow baking pan.
Pare, core and quarter apples.
Cut every quarter into 2 pieces lengthwise.
Place in parallel rows on top of mixture with the sharp edge down.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: club cracker bars
directions: Slightly grease 9 x 13 pan. Boil the above ingredients 5 minutes; stir constantly. Line pan with Club crackers. Pour 1/2 of the filling on top of crackers. Press another row of crackers and then the other 1/2 of filling.

title: italian cassata* * * * *
directions: This recipe for Chicken Cacciatore came from Pisa, Italy where we camped on our trip through Italy.
The wine makes the difference.
I make homemade noodles to go with it and to serve.
I put the noodles on a large platter; top with the chicken and then the sauce.
Sprinkle with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.

title: easy tuna pie
directions: Pour each of the cans of tuna, mixed vegetables and cream soup in a large casserole.
Mix together and spread in dish.
Beat flour, milk and vegetable oil together.
Spoon on top of mixture in casserole.
Bake in oven at 375° until crust is nicely browned.

title: one pot ham and cheese bake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put chopped peppers in large pot.
Add vinegar.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix in sugar.
Add butter. Place over high heat. Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in pectin.
Bring back to a full boil.
Boil 1minute.
Stir constantly.
Ladle quickly into prepared sterilized jelly jars.
Fill to within 1/8-inch of top.
Screw tops.
Invert jars for 5 minutes, then turn upright.
Cool for 1 1/2 hours, then shake jars vigorously to distribute peppers throughout jelly.
Makes six 8-ounce jars. Serve over cream cheese.
Serve on crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugars, oil and eggs; beat until well blended.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Mix together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder; stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and lightly floured loaf tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and oil with a fork.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt; mix with a large spoon.
Cut apples in 1/8's.
Fold apples into batter.
Batter will be thick.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill and roll in balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: spicy percolator punch
directions: Put dry ingredients in top of percolator, liquid in the bottom and perk.
(Very rich.)
Recipe can be increased for large amount.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Roll Oreos into fine crumbs.
Put 1/2 of the crumbs in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup milk.
Set aside.
Cook until thick 3 cups milk, 4 beaten egg yolks, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Remove from stove and add gelatin.
Cool mixture.
When cold, add 4 beaten egg whites (beat until stiff) and Dream Whip which has been mixed according to directions.
Pour entire mixture into pan on top of cookie crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate until firm and ready to serve.

title: chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours.

title: sauce for pork
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add rest of ingredients; cook until bouillon is dissolved.
Pour half of sauce over pork roast the last 30 minutes of baking.
Pour remaining sauce over meat when serving.

title: applesauce cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and soda.
Mix butter, Sucaryl and egg until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and applesauce alternately mixing well after each addition.
Fold in raisins and cereal.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet, about 1 inch apart.
Bake 18 minutes.

title: apple dessert cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture; fold in nuts and apples.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream.

title: south of the border corn
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Cook corn according to package directions; transfer corn to a serving platter and brush margarine mixture over corn.

title: pear relish
directions: If red bell peppers are not available, use pimento.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, milk, chocolate and pinch of salt. Cook slowly until forms a firm ball when dropped in cold water; set aside until it warms slightly.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Beat until it begins to lose its glaze; pour out in pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut grapes and cherries into halves.
Drain mandarin oranges, pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix everything together and refrigerate.

title: pop-up pizza
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger and drain.
Stir in onion, green pepper, garlic, oregano, salt, water, hot pepper sauce, tomato sauce and sauce mix; simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: brown rice
directions: In casserole
dish
melt
butter.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake, covered, 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Boil beans in 2-quart saucepan with plenty of water for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let beans soak in pan with the water for at least 1 hour or overnight.
Rinse and drain beans.
Place in crock-pot, just covering with water.
Add carrots, celery, onion and ham.
Cook on low 5 to 8 hours.
Season before serving with salt and pepper.
Salt will slow softening of the beans, so add last.
Serve with crackers or soft rolls.

title: dark ham glaze
directions: In skillet combine all ingredients and bring to simmer, then turn off heat.
(Enough for 1 1/2 pound ham.)

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Core and seed peppers. Brown hamburger, onion, garlic, salt and pepper; drain. Add Minute rice and tomato sauce. Stuff mixture into pepper shells. Put in baking dish; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Uncover; add cheese. Return to oven until melted.

title: applesauce gelatin squares
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in cold water and applesauce. Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2 inch dish, coated with nonstick cooking spray. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Serves 16.

title: peach-glazed stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and dice peaches, reserving syrup. Mix water and margarine in bowl; stir in stuffing mix, peaches and syrup.
Fill pork chop pockets with stuffing mix.
Arrange chops in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix preserves and mustard; brush over chops. Bake 60 minutes or until cooked through.
Bake remaining stuffing in a casserole dish for 30 minutes.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: crunch "n" crackle
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, water and corn syrup.

Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Cook until hard crack stage (300°), or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water separates into threads which are hard and brittle.
Immediately remove from heat.
Stir in butter, soda, almond extract and cereal.
Pour into large, greased baking sheet.
Quickly spread mixture to about 1/4-inch thick. Cool; break into pieces.
Makes about 1 pound candy.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Rinse in cold water; drain well.
Add cukes, tomatoes, bell pepper, olives and onions.
Pour Italian dressing over mixture.
Mix well.
Best when set for awhile.

title: susan's wonderful cheese bread
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle dry yeast on warm water.
Stir in sugar and salt until dissolved.
Add 2 cups of the flour; beat well with spoon.
Add eggs, cheese and seeds (if used); beat well. Beat in 3 to 4 more cups flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface, cover with bowl and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead into dough enough of remaining flour to make a smooth elastic dough with small blisters over surface, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: frosting for flower decorations on cake
directions: Beat 7 to 10 minutes.
This should be dull, not shiny.
If large eggs are used, add more powdered sugar and beat longer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add liquid and 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Add rice and Velveeta cheese and cook until cheese is melted.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: date loaf cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together, then sift this over dates, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Add sugar and mix. Beat in yolks and fold in whites.
Cook in moderate oven about 1 hour.
Bake with cover the last 30 minutes.

title: pink cheese nut salad
directions: Drain pineapple; mix juice from pineapple with water to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello and sugar.
Cool about 5 or 10 minutes in refrigerator.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill in covered dish for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into large pan.
Cook over medium-low heat. Add onion.
Cook and stir until transparent.
Drain; discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Stir in milk; add seasonings.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Serve over biscuits. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Toss and brown sausage; drain on paper towels.
Pour off most of grease and cook pepper, onion and celery until tender.
Boil chicken soup mix and rice in
4 1/2 cups water for 7 minutes.
Put all together in a casserole dish and add almonds.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cup a cup a cup a
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in ungreased baking dish or pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares or scoop into dessert dishes and serve warm.
Delish with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add mashed potatoes and mix slightly beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Combine with syrup, milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and continue baking in moderate oven (325°) for 35 to 45 minutes longer.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and 2 cups of flour in pan.
Set aside.
Then mix all fruit together; put in other 2 cups of flour and all the spices.
Mix well together.
Then mix all together in one big pan.
You can use tube pans or loaf pans.
It will take 2 tube pans or 4 loaf pans.
Cook at 350° for 90 minutes to 2 hours.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Boil carrots, celery and onion in water 5 minutes.
Melt margarine in large pot; add flour and blend well.
Slowly add chicken broth, stirring constantly to prevent lumping, then add milk, Cheez Whiz, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Stir in mustard and the boiled vegetables including the water in which they were boiled.
Bring to a boil and serve.

title: mrs. s's sausage and spinach pie
directions: Remove casing from sausage; fry sausage and scramble.
Cool and pour off fat.
In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients with wooden spoon.
Make pie crusts.
Put into 10-inch deep pie glass dish.
Brush 1 egg white over top of pie crust and slit holes on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Add boiling water to raisins and let cool.
Mix flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and soda.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and beans until broken.
Add dry ingredients, cooled raisins, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Set aside.
Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Combine cheeses, eggs and oregano. Grease a 9 x 11-inch pan and layer, starting at the bottom sauce, noodles (3), cheese (1/2), sauce, noodles (3), cheese, noodles (last 3) and sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving to firm up.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Add 1 cup vinegar and 1/2 cup Wesson oil.
Bring to simmer. Cool.
Add vegetables; store in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.
Keeps well.

title: mexican green chili
directions: Bring water and bouillon to boil.
Add pork tenderloin and other ingredients.
Cook uncovered for 2 hours.
Serves at least 2 people.

title: tea punch
directions: Dissolve the sugar and tea in 1 cup boiling water. Add the remaining ingredients.

title: noodles and tomato sauce
directions: Let an adult cook the macaroni.
Mix macaroni and tomato sauce.
Eat!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stew and debone chicken breasts.
Add melted margarine, celery soup, peas and carrots and chicken broth from chicken.
Mix together and pour in baking dish.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Wash chicken breast in hot water to clean.
Squeeze a little lemon juice over and add a little salt and pepper to taste if you like.
(I personally never use salt, but some people really like the taste.)
Roast chicken at 350° until cooked, about 45 minutes. In the last ten minutes add salsa on top of breast.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve with a green vegetable.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter pie pans.
Mix ingredients, except soda.
Cook until peanuts pop.
Add soda when ready to take off stove.
Yields 6 to 7 patties.

title: reubenwich
directions: Mix
well and use!
Heat the extra sauce and serve with the Reuben.

title: quick lunch
directions: Combine soups and chicken.
Pour into shallow one pint casserole.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: If using orange Jell-O, you may also use 1 small can mandarin oranges, drained.

title: mee mee's fiesta soup
directions: Brown ground beef, until no longer pink.
Add onion, garlic and tomato products.
Allow to simmer on low for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Allow to simmer covered for 10 -12 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, salt and mace in a large mixing bowl.
Cream sugar mixture and butter until light and fluffy.
Add extracts.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add parts of flour and milk to creamed mixture alternately, blending well after each addition.

title: campside bean scramble
directions: Brown hamburger meat, put in ketchup, sugar, mustard and beans.
Add meat.
Heat to serve.

title: punch
directions: Combine jello, boiling water and sugar. Stir until dissolved. Add water, ginger ale, sherbet and ice cubes.
Add sliced lemons and oranges.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Do not mix.
Spread each ingredient into greased cake pan. Cut oleo sticks into small pads.
Layer over the top.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Line bottom with wax paper; grease paper.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda onto a sheet of wax paper.

title: party cheesecakes
directions: Place paper liners in muffin cups. Put one vanilla wafer in each.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients and beat until smooth.
Bake in oven at 350° for one hour.
Can be made the night before.
Serves 15.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Put 1/2 into bottom of 8 x 8-inch dish.
Mix first 3 ingredients and put 1/2 over cake, then remaining cake and rest of mix.
Top with cherry pie filling. Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix and add all other ingredients.
Shape into balls (if necessary chill dough).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Flatten with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil.
Sift confectioners sugar and cocoa into a 2-quart baking dish.
Add evaporated milk and butter.
Do not stir.
Place in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High or until butter just melts.
Add vanilla. Stir until all ingredients are well blended.
Turn fudge into an aluminum foil-lined pan.
Smooth top.
Place in freezer for 10 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 64.

title: manhattan pudding
directions: Mix gelatin with a little water.
Add juices, rind and sugar (stir).
Place in an ice cube tray and leave until almost hard. Put whipped cream on top.
Add a little confectioners sugar and chopped walnuts (about a cup).
Place on top and freeze.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil and boil for 5 minutes (watch pot so the mixture doesn't boil over).
Remove from stove.
Add 1 pint of the cheapest brandy you can get.
Bottle and wait 30 days before using.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and hot water.
Add pineapple and softened cream cheese.
After mixing, refrigerate.
Let set until thickened. Mix Dream Whip as stated and add to thickened jello.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: italian country chicken
directions: Heat oil in heavy, large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until translucent, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Add chicken and stir until cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Mix in artichoke hearts with liquid, peppers with liquid and olives and heat through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over pasta and toss well.
Serve, passing Parmesan separately.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: french bread spread
directions: Mix together and spread on French bread that is cut lengthwise.
Wrap halves in foil leaving top open.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Slice with electric knife.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 24 hours, stirring often.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients except peas in a 4 1/2 to 5-quart saucepan. Bake at 250° for 5 hours. Add peas and stir after 3 1/2 hours.

title: lemon spread
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together sugar, egg and lemon juice. Add butter.
Without letting mixture boil, cook over moderately low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Cover and chill about 1 hour or store for several days. Mixture thickens as it cools.

title: dolly bread
directions: Pour a little oil in skillet.
Sprinkle with corn meal.
Bake at 400°.

title: pecan pumpkin crumble
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine spice, eggs, sugar, pumpkin and evaporated milk.
Blend well.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Drizzle evenly with melted butter.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: moistest ever coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Make 2 layers.
While cake is baking, mix sour cream, sugar and coconut.
When cake has cooled, split the layers.
Put coconut mixture between layers and on top of cake.
Best if made the day before.

title: uncooked chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil, then add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Chill.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Melt butter, add cheese and melt into butter.
Put broccoli and hamburger in crockpot.
Add cheese/margarine mixture.
stir well.
Heat on low for about 4 hours, stirring once in a while. It will seem thin at first, but will thicken up.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crumble
vanilla wafers fine, cut dates fine, chop nuts and cut
cherries.
Mix all together including coconut.
Pour milk over all and mix well.
Press in container; store in cool place.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook hen until tender.
In large skillet saute onions, celery and bell pepper until light brown.
Add 3 cups broth, tomato paste and mushroom soup.
Cook slowly about 40 minutes.
Add deboned chicken and 1 package vermicelli spaghetti (prepared per package instructions).
Cook just long enough to get hot through.
Just before serving, grate cheese on top and melt in oven.

title: fish fillets supreme
directions: Brown the onion in butter; then mix with crumbs, salt and seasonings.
Add 1/2 cup Borden salad dressing.
Cut fillets in uniform strips.
Spread with bread stuffing; roll jelly roll fashion.
Place in large greased muffin pans.
Spread with remaining salad dressing, then bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with extra salad dressing.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Dip clusters of grapes in egg white. Set aside to dry.
When nearly dry, sprinkle with sugar.
Good snack after school.

title: taco dip
directions: Microwave cheeses; mix together until creamy and smooth.
Add tomatoes and drained sausage; mix well.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: fudge
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; mix in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Add vanilla and nuts. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Pour fudge into pan and cool until firm.
Cut in squares and store in cool place.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients. Mix well. Place in loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: party cake
directions: Bake cake 15 minutes in
9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with 2 cups milk.
Add pudding.
Beat until thick.
Pour over cooked cake.
Then spread pineapple or banana or blueberries on top.
Cover with Cool Whip and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and form into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: quiche bretagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine mayonnaise, salt, eggs, milk and wine.
Mix until well blended.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add cheese, crabmeat, celery and onion to mayonnaise mixture; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix flours, cornmeal, baking soda and salt together.
Add raisins and nuts.
Slowly add buttermilk and molasses alternately to dry ingredients after each addition.
Pour into buttered 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, or tested done.
Let stand in pan on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Loosen side with knife; turn out on rack.
Brush with butter while still warm.
Cool before cutting.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients sprinkle over pie and return to oven and bake 10 minutes.
Or till crumbs are brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Chop onion, celery and green pepper.
Brown ground beef with onion, celery and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer approximately 1 hour.

title: seven layer vegetable salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer in the following order:
celery, green pepper, onion, peas and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, cream and egg.
Add salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix in flour.
Roll out mixture to 1/4-inch thick and cut out with floured cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Cool and decorate.
Enjoy!

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Bring to a full boil sugar, butter and cream.
Boil 7 to 9 minutes or until it forms a soft ball.
Take off the heat, then add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).

title: mounds-type bars
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Sprinkle coconut over crust.
Pour milk over coconut.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top should be slightly brown.
Melt chocolate chips over low heat or in microwave and spread over warm bars.
If chocolate is stiff, add a little margarine.
Yields 15 to 20 bars.

title: homemade soup mix
directions: Mix together well and store.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Chop zucchini into about 1/4-inch slices.
Cook until tender. In meantime, brown ground meat and drain.
Mix spaghetti sauce, cooked zucchini and ground meat.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Stir together other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill.
(Can remain in refrigerator for several weeks.)

title: chicken curry
directions: Cut up broilers, if using wings, remove tips, cut wings in half.
Mix the other ingredients with the melted butter.
Dip chicken in the mixture.
Place in greased pan.
Bake 1 hour or more in 375° oven.
You may use the tips to make soup stock if you wish.
Serve with rice and vegetables for dinner.
The wings can be used as hors d'oeuvres with a beverage or cocktails.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion until crisp in vegetable oil.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir in celery and onion mixture, cheese, broccoli and rice.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat until nearly done. Add all spices and potato. Cook on low heat until done. Stir often to keep from sticking.
Heat sauce to a boil. Dip tortillas in sauce and cover bottom of casserole dish (about 6).
Put a layer of meat and cheese. Top with olives.
Repeat. Cook until cheese on top melts.

title: simply sensational salsa
directions: In medium size bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Salsa will get hotter the longer it stands.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: wheat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Serve with pieces of pita bread.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine water, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and 1 cup pineapple juice drained from chunks.
(If there is not a cup of juice, add water to make a cup.)
Cook in a large saucepan until it is clear and slightly thickened.
Keep sauce warm.
Heat oil to 375°.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then coat with flour.
Deep fry pieces until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Add pineapple, green pepper and carrot to sauce; heat.
Add chicken; heat briefly again.
Serve over hot rice.

title: easy rolls
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Add shortening and mix until consistency of corn meal.
Add sugar and yeast to warm water. Stir until dissolved.
Add to flour mixture.
Turn onto floured board; knead well.
Make into desired shapes; brush tops with butter.
Allow to rise for about 1 1/2 hours in a warm place until double in bulk.
Bake in preheated 450° oven.

title: very-berry fruit salad
directions: About 2 hours before serving, gently toss strawberries with sugar in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, gently toss all berries together.
In medium bowl, mix ice cream and orange peel.
Mix and serve over berries.
Serve in glass bowls to enjoy all the great colors.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Sift together sugar and cocoa; add cheese and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well. Spread evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cut in pieces. Makes 6 1/2 pounds.

title: geri's beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain well and set aside.
Mix together tomatoes, water, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, bay leaf, cabbage, onion, celery, Worcestershire sauce and mixed vegetables.
Cook on low to medium heat for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add kidney beans and beef to soup and simmer for 30 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter rice krispies squares
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar and syrup in medium heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil over low heat and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly, to keep from sticking.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, green peppers and carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Drain mixture if water accumulates.

title: fast and low-fat codfish cakes
directions: Open can and remove codfish whole.
Slice into 4 portions. Lightly brush frying pan with oil and heat on medium-high.
(May be coated with flour or cornmeal if desired.)
Fry well until browned.
Turn once (may need to recoat pan with oil) and brown second side.
Good with boiled potatoes, stewed tomatoes and cornbread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain grease.
Put hot broccoli in mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Saute onion in margarine.
Dip onion out; reserve margarine.
Add onion to broccoli.
Add mushroom soup to broccoli and mix well.
Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Saute crushed crackers in margarine (add another 1/2 stick margarine, if needed).
Put Ritz crackers on top of casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey heavenly hash
directions: Mix the 2 teaspoons pineapple juice with Miracle Whip.
Mix all ingredients together.
(Much better when fixed 6 or 8 hours before serving.)

title: carrot cake(use "glaze" or "icing" topping)
directions: Place all dry goods in a bowl and add oil and eggs.
Mix together.
Add carrots and nuts, blend. Pour mixture into ungreased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add cooled milk (lukewarm), shortening, 3/4 cup sugar and salt.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Let stand 10 minutes. Knead lightly on floured board.
Flour surface of dough until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Grease lid and cover. Store in refrigerator as long as you wish.
Bring from refrigerator about 2 hours before you shape into rolls.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in hot oven at 400° to 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Punch down unused dough and return to fridge.

title: syrup cake
directions: Combine syrup, eggs, and sugar; mix well. Stir in oil and coffee; beat well. Gradually stir in rest of ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until center springs back when lightly pressed.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Cook the beef until mostly done with the onion, then add the remaining ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Butter an 8 x 10-inch pan generously.
Roll fish fillets in flour and lay side by side in pan.
Dot with butter or margarine and pour evaporated milk over to just about cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: quick yogurt pie
directions: Thoroughly mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell and chill 15 to 30 minutes (or longer).
Garnish if desired.
Serves 6.
This is simple, but elegant!

title: heavenly layer cake
directions: Spread over base and then.

title: poached chicken breasts
directions: In skillet, combine juice, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken and bring to boil again.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer gently 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serve over a bed or rice accompanied by a tossed salad.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve first three ingredients and mix well.
When slightly cooled, add remaining ingredients.
Chill until partly set, then stir good.
Chill until firm.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With fork or pastry cutter, mix together first four ingredients.
In separate dish, beat remaining ingredients. Combine two mixtures until all ingredients are moistened.
Mold with hands until mixture is smooth.
Makes approximately 5 single crusts.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix dates, nuts and peanut butter together.
With your hands wet in cold water, shape these into tiny balls about the size of a marble.
Make an icing with cream or milk and powdered sugar.
Dip each ball into the icing and, while icing is still wet, roll in coconut.
Place each ball on waxed paper and place in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
This makes approximately 30 (1-inch in diameter).

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to a boil, pineapple, sugar and jello.
Let cool until set.
Add all other ingredients, reserving a few chopped nuts to sprinkle on top.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set and cut into squares.
Can be made 3 to 4 days in advance.
It keeps very well.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine softened cream
cheese, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg, mixing well until blended.
Mash 3/4 cup strawberries.
Stir into cream cheese mixture.
Whip cream with confectioners sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fold remaining strawberries into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with additional strawberries.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in sour cream, celery salt and Tabasco at least 2 hours before cooking.

title: rice-bean salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and mustard together.
Stir in the rice and add the beans, vegetables and the hard-cooked eggs.
Cover and put in the refrigerator until chilled.
Contains 330 calories.

title: pull apart coffee cake
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter and remove from heat. Cut
each roll into quarters.
Add these to skillet and toss
with butter.
Add
white sugar, orange rind, nutmeg and walnuts.

title: baked quail
directions: Salt and pepper quail inside and out.
Combine mushrooms, bread crumbs, salt, cayenne pepper and truffles.
Saute in butter.
Stuff quail with this mixture.

title: sausage finger sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain.
Add shredded Velveeta. Spread onto party rye.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze, then put in Ziploc bags.
Pull out number you want and broil until bubbly and brown.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening and add to all ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Chill for 3 hours. Form into balls, roll in sugar. Bake in batches at 375° for 8-10 minutes.

title: glazed teriyaki salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients (except salmon) in a shallow dish. Marinate salmon for about 30 minutes, turning once. Remove salmon from marinade, reserving marinade. Place salmon in 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Remove from oven; keep warm! Bring reserved marinade to a boil in a small saucepan. Cook, stirring often, 6-8 minutes or until reduced by half. Pour over salmon. Salmon can also be grilled instead of baked. Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, sugar and pour in graham cracker crust.
Cook blueberries.
Sweeten to taste.
Thicken with corn starch.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Cool and pour mixture.
Top with whipped cream or cool whip.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding into large Cool Whip thoroughly.
Add drained crushed pineapple and mini marshmallows.
Refrigerate. Serve when ready.

title: chicken-broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in
a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Stir-fry chicken and garlic for 3 to 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Reduce heat.
Remove chicken and keep warm. Stir in broccoli and red pepper. Cover and steam 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: herbed tomato quiche
directions: Blend the flour, butter, salt and lemon rind until the mixture looks like cornmeal.
Sprinkle the liquid over the dough; toss lightly with a fork and gather into a firm ball.
Press the ball into a flat round; wrap in wax paper and then in a plastic bag and chill for at least 30 minutes.

Roll gently into a 13-inch round; roll pastry around rolling pin and unroll over quiche mold. Carefully push pastry on sides down against base where it meets sides to thicken and strengthen so shell can stand unmolded.
Trim excess off top or roll under to form a narrow lip.

Prick the bottom of the shell with a fork and chill or freeze for 1 hour. Then line the shell with buttered foil; weight down with rice or beans and bake in bottom third of hot oven (400°) for about 15 minutes or until it begins to set.
Carefully remove foil and bake another 10 to 15 minutes or until it is lightly colored.
Remove shell from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: cherry pie
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Pour half of mixture into greased 7 x 12-inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over mixture.
Top with remaining crumbly mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: After cooking chicken, strain broth for small bones.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth as directed.
Saute celery, onion, green pepper and mushrooms in butter or bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in baking dish; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage stir-fry
directions: Cook potatoes in a covered pot in boiling salted water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine 2 tablespoons water, teriyaki sauce and cornstarch; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in hot oil for 1 minute.
Add cabbage.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add potatoes. Stir-fry another 2 minutes.
Add teriyaki mixture and parsley. Cook for 1 minute.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: In a bowl combine macaroni and cheese, celery, tomato, mayonnaise, onion, pickles and mustard.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with sliced eggs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soft icing
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat at moderate speed for 2 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine and let stand overnight.
Next day, add whipped cream. Add nuts, if desired.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 2 rolls and refrigerate overnight or freeze.
Slice to 1/2-inch thick and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: country pork 'n sauerkraut
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ribs and onion in oil until ribs are browned and onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until ribs are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: In a large bowl, combine the zucchini, onion and mushrooms.
In a medium bowl, mix together the cornstarch and 1 tablespoon of the milk, then stir in the remaining milk.
Beat in the eggs and seasonings.
Stir the egg mixture into the vegetables, then stir in the cheese.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: grilled roast beef sandwiches
directions: Preheat skillet over medium heat and melt 2 tsp. of margarine.
Saute onions and mushrooms until golden.
Next saute slices of roost beef until darkened.
Remove from pan.
Mix mayonnaise & dijon together in small bowl.
Spread mixture on inside of one slide of the bread.
Layer 2 slices of roast beef then 2-3 slices of grilled onion and mushrooms.
Add slice of cheese and 2 more slices of roast beef. Butter both sides of bread before grilling.
Grill sandwich on medium heat until golden brown on both sides and cheese is melted.
(If individuals don't like any of the ingredients - they can be deleted.)

title: venison and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; add venison, onion and seasonings.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned.
Add tomatoes; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Carnation milk, butter and salt.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Put in a large mixing bowl the following: chocolate chips, Marshmallow creme, nuts and chocolate squares.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolate is all melted.
Pour in pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix all ingredients together until blended. Refrigerate for a couple of hours. Serve with fresh strawberries, sliced apples or any fresh fruit you like.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Heat syrup and sugar to dissolve sugar.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies; stir well.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pickle relish
directions: Mix green pepper, onion, bell pepper, garlic salt, dill seed and sliced cukes; put in jars.
Pour the sugar, vinegar and coarse salt over the ingredients in jars.

title: sesame seed chicken
directions: In baking dish cover chicken with soy sauce.
Sprinkle sesame seed on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour. Very easy.

title: diced green chile dip
directions: Heat all ingredients together in chafing dish or fondue pot over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with corn chips. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: caramel pecan rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in 1/4 sugar, salt, 2 tablespoons margarine, egg and 2 cups of flour; beat until smooth.
With spoon or hand, work in enough remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Place greased side up in greased bowl.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 4 or 5 days.

title: i've got a secret cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add cottage cheese, beets, pineapple, coconut and nuts, mixing well after each addition.
Beat for 1 minute.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan (pan will be very full).
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes (cake gets very brown).
Cool and frost with favorite icing.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Mix flour and flavorings.
Blend in 7-Up.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; add oil and beat well.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Gradually add buttermilk, figs, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
While warm, stick holes in cake with fork and glaze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 small loaf pans. Peel and cut bananas and beat with mixer.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Alternately add the dry ingredients in thirds and the mashed bananas and buttermilk twice and beat.
Add nuts.
Pour into prepared pans and bake for about 45 minutes or until tests done.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup Parmesan, oregano, garlic powder and pepper; roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange skin side down in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; turn chicken and bake 20 minutes more.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Pat mixture evenly in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs together.
Pour over other mixture. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches; cover with sugar. Let stand several hours. Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan. Beat remaining ingredients and pour over peaches. Bake at 400°.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and cocoa well in a medium saucepan. Stir in milk gradually until smooth.
Cook over medium low heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Let stand. Meanwhile, beat egg yolks and add a little of cooked mixture. Blend well, then add egg mixture to the cooked mixture.
Stir until you have the right consistency.
Pour filling into cooled baked pie shell; cover with meringue.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, oil, eggs and 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk.
Put 1/2 of the batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put all ingredients except rice and sausage in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add sausage in the last 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, flour, baking powder, soda, salt, milk and vanilla.
Mix well; fold in cubed apples. Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sugar mixture.

title: cardinal casserole
directions: In medium size bowl, mix bread crumbs, bird seed and grapes (cut up); set aside.
Put suet through meat grinder, then melt in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Cool until slightly hardened. Reheat and pour 1 1/2 cups over dry ingredients.
Add sand; mix well.
Turn into a foil loaf size pan.
Refrigerate until firm. Place on feeder tray.

title: cape cod indian pudding
directions: Add cornmeal to scalded milk.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Mix in everything but the eggs and last cup of milk.
Let pudding cool, then add beaten eggs.

title: three cheese broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch.
Mix baking mix, onion, milk and 2 eggs; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Spread in dish.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook the grits in the boiling water until dry (follow directions on the grits box). Cook in a pot large enough that you will be able to add the other ingredients. When grits are cooked, remove from heat and add the cheese, beaten eggs, butter and salt to the grits. Stir well. Spray baking dish with Pam. Pour into the large baking dish (at least 1 1/2-quart size). Sprinkle some extra cheese on top (I sometimes sprinkle a little Parmesan along with the Cheddar on top). Bake at 350° for one hour. Serves 6.

title: salad dressing
directions: Fill measuring cup shaker, to 1/4 c. line with water or olive oil, fill to 1/3 line with vinegar, and fill to 2/3 line with sugar.
Shake well and add to salad or slaw.
Excellent for slaw or tossed salad.

title: broccoli ring or casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until tender. Drain water and whip with electric mixer.
Cool.
Add to well beaten eggs; mix in all other ingredients.
Beat until smooth with mixer.
Pour into buttered ring or casserole.
Set in a pan of water and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Good hot or cold.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut beef stew into small pieces.
Salt, pepper and flour generously.
Brown meat in about 3 tablespoons shortening.
Pour gravy sauce over beef with equal parts of hot water (pour into bottle to remove all gravy sauce as it is molasses and adheres to bottle).
Braise over low heat about 1/2 hour, then add vegetables. Open both cans of bean sprouts and use the liquid to thin as needed.
Add the bean sprouts last as they only need to be heated up and will remain firm.
If more liquid is needed during stewing time, use water.

title: yum yum
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pour in a pan.
Now mix next 3 ingredients together.
Pour over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger and fixings sandwiches
directions: Cook beef until browned.
Spoon off fat.
Meanwhile, toast French bread.
Stir soup, ketchup, pickle, mustard and pepper into skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat through. Divide been mixture into loaf.
Top with desired toppings.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Season shrimp with salt and pepper; set aside.
Melt margarine in skillet; add onions, celery and tomato paste.
Cook slowly, uncovered, until onions are wilted.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to mixture.
Add shrimp and cook for 20 minutes; serve over rice.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Cut up lettuce.
Wash spinach; cut off stems and chop.
Mix lettuce and spinach together.
Combine the sugar and salt. Sprinkle 1/2 of the sugar-salt mixture over the greens.
