(If desired, set aside some of the bacon and boiled eggs for garnish.) Now, layer the onion, bacon, boiled eggs and peas on top of the greens.
Stir the remaining sugar-salt mixture into the mayonnaise and spread evenly over the salad, "sealing off" the top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: red hot applesauce salad
directions: Combine boiling water with red hots in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat to dissolve.
Remove from heat; stir in Jell-O. Blend in applesauce.
Pour half of the mixture into 2-quart mold or 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Blend softened cream cheese with mayonnaise; add nuts.
Spread cheese mixture over chilled mixture.
Pour (gently) remaining Jell-O mixture over cheese and chill until firm.

title: apple filled acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut squash in half lengthwise and scrape out seeds.
Place cut side down in baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: "the next best thing to robert redford"
directions: Blend the flour, butter and pecans.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Beat the cream cheese, sugar and half of Cool Whip until blended. Spread over the cooled crust.
Blend together the chocolate and vanilla pudding and milk and pour over the cream cheese layer. Spread the remaining Cool Whip on top.
Finely chopped pecans can be sprinkled on top.

title: pork spinach pie
directions: Place frozen pie shell on a baking sheet; do not prick. Bake in	a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce temperature
Sprinkle cheese in bottom of pie shell; set aside.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Place in blender.
In separate bowl, combine hot water and sugar, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add lemon juice and pour into blender.
Puree until smooth.
Pour into plastic cups.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Remove and break up mixture with a spoon until slushy.
Return to freezer for 1 hour.
Remove and break up mixture with a spoon until slushy.
Return to freezer for another hour or until desired firmness is reached.
Break up mixture with a spoon to serve.
If slush cups are frozen solid, microwave for 15 to 20 seconds to soften as desired.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except biscuit and cheese.
Put beef mixture in an 8-inch pan.
Roll out biscuits and cover beef, mixed ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, then cover with grated cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza on rye
directions: In separate pans, brown meats.
Do not cook together.
Drain meats in colander, then on paper towel.
Drain completely.
Cut Velveeta in cubes; combine with meats in pan.
Melt cheese; add spices.
Blend and spread on rye bread and place in freezer on cookie sheet until set.
Broil on
lowest rack of oven until brown.
Store in Ziploc bags and use as needed.
Good for a quick snack after square dancing.

title: salmon sauce
directions: Heat and stir.
Do not boil.
Serve over grilled salmon.

title: broccoli-onion casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli until tender.
In another saucepan, cook the onions in boiling, salted water until tender;
drain each. In saucepan, melt 1/8 cup of margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and dash
of
pepper
if
desired.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly,
until
thick
and bubbly.
Reduce heat; add cream cheese
and stir until smooth.
Mix the sauce into the vegetables. Turn
into
a
greased
casserole and top with shredded cheese. Melt
cup
of
margarine
and mix with the bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: eggplant and ampalaya gulay
directions: Slice eggplants and ampalayas like finger size or lengthwise into 4 to 6 slices.
Place lemon grass in bottom of saucepan. Place ampalaya slices and eggplant on top and cook until desired doneness, crisp, tender or soft.
When done, add coconut milk, salt or patis (fish sauce).
Season as desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake
in greased casserole at 375° until lightly brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and pepper.
Slowly blend in liquid and vinegar.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Add beets and heat.

title: southern living fruit bowl
directions: Place fruit in a large bowl in order:
peaches, pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Mix dry pudding and Tang and gently fold with fruit.
Let stand several hours before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 9 items and then add pumpkin, raisins and nuts. Bake in 4 greased 1-pound coffee cans at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool and remove from cans.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add sour cream, eggs, and vanilla to butter.
Blend on low. Add flour mixture.
Blend on low, then beat 3 minutes at
medium. Pour
into
greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overcook. Cool and ice. Serves 12 to 15.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
In another mixing bowl, cream butter and cream cheese, both at room temperature.
Should look fluffy.
Add sugar one cup at a time and beat well after each. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, and beat well.
Add vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon almond.
Fold in egg whites. Bake in a Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or bake in smaller pans at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Bake until done; take out of pan immediately!

title: monkey bread by marian
directions: Cut biscuits in half and make balls.
Place sugar and cinnamon in a Baggie.
Mix well.
Drag balls in mix to coat.
Place in fluted pan; fill pan.
Pour melted butter over biscuits, then sprinkle the remainder of sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow to cool.
Turn over on plate and walk past and pull off a piece.
Enjoy!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Divide dough in half; shape and place in lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light and puffy.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 2 round layer pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan(s).

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add egg yolks 1 at a time to shortening and sugar, beating thoroughly after each one added.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk and vanilla to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pans (greased) and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: potato bread
directions: Peel potatoes; cook in boiling water until done.
Mash in liquid.
Remove two cups and heat until warm.
Add yeast to 1/4 cup of potato mixture.
To remaining 1 3/4 cups potatoes, add shortening, sugar and salt.
Add yeast mixture and 1/2 cup flour. Beat.
Gradually add remaining flour.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over rice and herbs.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Add soup, mushrooms with liquid, water and seasonings.
Mix and let stand.
Saute the onions in the 3 tablespoons oil until glossy.
Add to casserole with the oil.
Brown the meat and add to casserole.
Mix all together.
Cover with foil; refrigerate.
When ready to bake, keep it covered and bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Put cranberries, sugar and salt in blender with enough orange juice to engage blender.
Combine with marshmallows and chill overnight.
Add remaining ingredients and fold in whipped cream. Garnish with clusters of green grapes and fresh cranberries, if desired.

title: nippy franks sauce
directions: Cook ingredients together over low heat.
Add cocktail wieners.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cook in crock-pot.
Cut steak into serving pieces.
Season flour.
Dredge steak in flour.
Place onions in crock-pot; add meat.
Top with carrots and celery; cover with sauce.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours, or on high for 3 to 5 hours.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all
together.
Mix dry ingredients, then add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill cans
a little over half full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 cans.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and blend soup with milk.
Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and spices. Add to the pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins or dates. Pour into two 2-quart, greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
For best flavor, bake the day before serving.

title: gram's homemade pickles
directions: Boil the water, salt and vinegar in small pot.
Meanwhile, place cucumbers, pickling spice, dill, garlic clove and mustard seed in sealable glass jar.
Once liquids are boiled, place into jar and seal tightly.
Let sit until cool.
Once cooled, place in refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks or until desired crunch.

title: crispy pepper skin duckling
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and rub the mixture on the surface and in the cavity of the duckling.
Marinate for 30 minutes. Steam the duckling over high heat for 2 hours or until soft.
Remove. While the duckling is still hot, rub it with 1 tablespoon soy sauce.

title: refrigerator soup
directions: Use canned broth or a favorite canned soup as a base.
Add meat and vegetables from previous meals.
Simmer until heated. Add pasta or rice if desired.
Serve with salad and bread. Delicious!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Pour sugar into bowl.
Melt butter and chocolate.
Add to sugar and rest of ingredients.
Pat into greased pan.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 12-inch pan melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Top evenly with coconut, then sweetened condensed milk.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown. In small saucepan melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Spread evenly over hot coconut layer.
Cool 30 minutes.
Chill thoroughly; cut into small squares.
Garnish with nuts while hot, if desired.
Store loosely at room temperature.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Blend in ice cream with milk lightly.
Add pudding mix.
Beat for 1 minute or until mixed.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze for 1 hour or longer.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Make a white sauce.
Put in broiler until browned at 350°, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Sift well together flour, salt and baking powder.
Rub in shortening as lightly as possible with fingers, working just until well blended.
Then mix to a very soft dough with milk.
Mix with spoon or hand.
Turn the dough onto a well-floured board and roll out or pat 3/4-inch thick.
Cut biscuits and lay on baking pan not touching.
Bake in a quick oven (400°) for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Measure oatmeal, nuts, peanut butter and vanilla; set aside. Combine sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add first ingredients.
Mix quickly.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: cranberry-orange muffins
directions: Cut the cranberries in half and set them aside.

title: st. pat's lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, 1 cup boiling water, drained can of pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix in small carton of Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: russian chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Mix preserves, dressing and soup mix in a bowl thoroughly.
Place chicken in a greased baking dish. Pour the sauce over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40-50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Mix soup, hamburger and 1 cup milk together.
Spread mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread Tater Tots over top of mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until Tater Tots are done.

title: three-in-one sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer on low speed until smooth.
Pour into aluminum ice tray and freeze, stirring once or twice during freezing.
After frozen, sherbet can be put into another container.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease pizza pan well.
Slice cookie roll.
Place slices close in pan to cover, spreading to make the crust.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a plastic bag combine lemon juice, oil, garlic and bouillon. Add chicken (I like to cut my chicken into strips).
Marinate in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade; grill, broil or quick-fry basting with marinade.
Slice into strips after cooking if marinated whole.
Place chicken strips on warmed tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Garnish as desired.
Fold and serve immediately.

title: sauerkraut and ribs
directions: In a crock-pot put pork ribs, sauerkraut, potatoes and carrots.
Cook on high for a couple of hours, then turn down to low and cook the rest of the day.
If company drops in, just add more potatoes and carrots.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Shred beef with food processor.
Add onion, Accent and Worcestershire sauce to cream cheese.
Add 2/3 of the dried beef.
Shape into 2 or 3 balls and roll in the other 1/3 of the shredded dried beef.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons butter.
Add flour, blending well.
Pour milk in gradually, blending well.
Bring to a boil.
Add cheese and remove from heat, but keep warm.
Melt remaining butter in another pan.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and carrots, all of which have been finely chopped or grated.
Cook until transparent, then pass these through a sieve.
Add chicken stock and mix well. Combine two mixtures and season with hot pepper sauce and salt. Do not boil.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown onions and hamburger.
Add other ingredients; simmer. Can add beans, if desired.

title: new york cheese cake(serves 12)
directions: Melt chocolate.
Set aside.
Whip the cream cheese; add vanilla, Kahlua, 3/4 cup sugar and egg yolks.
Blend in chocolate.

title: jambalaya
directions: Put all ingredients in the rice cooker and turn on.
Yes, it's that easy.

title: gooey butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixer until well blended. Chill dough. Roll in small balls. Roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all together with oil, garlic, salt and oregano.

title: low-fat strawberry delite
directions: Cut angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Pour into large bowl.
Mix glaze and Cool Whip well, then pour onto cake and mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening, using a double boiler.
Remove from heat, but keep over warm water.
Drop pretzels, one at a time, into chocolate mixture.
Lift out with fork, tapping off the excess.
Place pretzels on wire rack over waxed paper to catch drips.
Allow to dry.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix the first 4 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Mix well.
Beat in with a fork one at a time the eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients in.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan lined with unbaked pastry.
Bake in center of oven until firm (or about 50 minutes).
Cool before serving.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1 tablespoon sugar and margarine together and spread evenly in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan which has been sprayed with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: raisin spice bars
directions: Simmer raisins in 1 cup water.
Save 4 tablespoons of water. Melt butter.
Add sugar and 4 tablespoons raisin water; blend. Stir in flour, soda and spices.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add drained raisins.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl and mix with spoon.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and 2 cups corn flakes.
Sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: While mixing other ingredients, soak 1 cup of 100% bran in 1 cup of boiling water.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together and add to the buttermilk mixture.
Add to this the soaked bran, 2 cups Kellogg's All-Bran and the raisins.
Bake in well-greased and floured muffin tin. Bake at 400°
for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep 3 weeks in refrigerator.
Fill tins about 3/4 full.
Makes 36 muffins.

title: e-z beef burgundy
directions: Put everything into casserole dish or pan that has tight-fitting cover.
Bake at 325° for at least 1 1/2 hours.
(May cook longer and it improves rather than spoils the dish.)
Serve over buttered noodles or rice.

title: javanese cookies
directions: Let butter get very soft; mix with sugar.
Add flour and coconut.
Mix with hands and form into 2 rolls.
Wrap with plastic; put in refrigerator to harden.

title: "big orange"  party punch
directions: Add to cans of water or crushed ice to the first 3 ingredients, mix well.
Add all ingredients except sherbet and stir together.
Then add sherbet and stir again.

title: sallie creech pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add syrup, nuts, salt and vanilla. Place in unbaked pie shell and bake for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: lacy french fried onion rings
directions: First, blend the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Next, combine the egg, oil and milk in a bowl and beat until thoroughly blended.
Beat in the dry ingredients until batter is smooth. Cover and set aside while preparing onions.
Can use to fry shrimp, also.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Blend
together
sugar,
catsup,
salt, paprika, celery seed and grated onion.
Add vinegar and salad oil alternately in small amounts and beat well.

title: sweet sugarless cupcakes
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Beat egg, water, sugar substitute, oil and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Divide batter evenly into 8 fluted paper baking cups placed in muffin tin. Set muffin pan in shallow pan of water and cover with inverted cake pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove pan cover and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 8.

title: brunch strata
directions: Trim crusts off 12 slices bread.
From center of each slice cut doughnut and holes with cutter.
Break remainder of bread in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover bread with 10 slices of sharp process cheese.
Next layer add thinly sliced water chestnuts.
Next add package of broccoli, cooked and drained.
Add ham.
Arrange bread doughnuts and holes on top. Combine eggs, milk, onions, salt and mustard.
Pour over mixture. Cover and refrigerate 6 to 12 hours.
Bake, uncovered, 55 minutes at 325°.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Fill doughnut holes with sprig of parsley.

title: "7-up frosted salad"
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in 7-Up.
Chill until partly set.
Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Fold pineapple, marshmallows and bananas into jello mixture.
Chill until firm. Add topping and chill overnight.

title: caesar salad
directions: Cover frypan lightly with olive oil.
Toast cubed bread in frypan, tossing in oil to coat.
Toast evenly.
Set aside when done.
Dust large bowl with garlic clove (rub garlic cut in half all around inside bowl).
Add romaine lettuce; tear into smaller pieces.
Pour oil (about 1/2 cup) over lettuce.
Season with salt and pepper; toss to coat evenly.
Make a well in lettuce in bowl. Add 1 raw egg and juice of 1/2 lemon.
Toss until all lettuce is evenly coated with a milky look.
Add about 3/4 cup Kraft Parmesan cheese; toss evenly again.
Add toasted bread; toss and serve immediately.

title: cookie pudding
directions: Dip cookies in milk. Layer cookies in a casserole or pan. Cover with Cool Whip. Alternate cookies and Cool Whip. Crumble 2 cookies on top. Refrigerate overnight. Prep time: 10 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-quart glass measuring cup, stir together white sugar and Karo syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove and add peanuts; stir well.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well and microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy. Pour mixture at once into buttered cookie sheet.
Cool for 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: cream of pumpkin soup
directions: Seed pumpkin, then pare off skin.
Cut into 1-inch pieces. Put in saucepan; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer until tender.
Strain and puree.
Put back in pan.
Reserve 1/4 cup of milk, then add remaining milk and water to pan.
Bring to a simmer.
Mix flour with reserved milk; stir into pan.
Continue to simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend in butter and season.
Serve with a bit of sugar on top.

title: mother's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and brown sugar; add egg. Add dry mixture, oats, flour, salt and cinnamon. Alternate with milk mixture of soda, milk and vanilla. Add chopped pecans and raisins. Drop by teaspoon full on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn beef dinner
directions: Take meat from package and rinse well.
Barely cover brisket with hot water.
Add onions and seasonings, cover and simmer about 1 hour per pound or until tender.
Remove meat from liquid, add potatoes and carrots, cover, bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes. Add cabbage and cook 20 minutes more.
Glaze cooked meat top with mustard and brown sugar.
Put in oven and bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
Don't skip this step.
It dries the meat out.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Saute onions.
Combine potatoes and water; cook 15 minutes or until potatoes feel tender.
Blend in soup, half of bacon pieces, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: swiss apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: watermelon pickle
directions: Put water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spices into a pan and boil for 3 minutes.
Put remaining ingredients into jar and then add boiled water mixture.
Close jars and place jars into water bath.
Boil until green pepper changes color.

title: sour cream cabbage
directions: Shred the cabbage fine.
Cook in as little water as possible until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain, then add the other ingredients; mix together.
Heat thoroughly on low heat.

title: stress-beating smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients into blender and whip.

title: mushroom and string bean quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms until crisp and brown.
Butter cooked beans and add mushrooms.
Season.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Roll refrigerated rolls into buttered 9 x 13 pan. Press seams tight. Cook and drain sausage. Sprinkle sausage on crescent rolls. Sprinkle cheese over the sausage. Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over top and bake at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes until crust is golden. Let sit to settle before cutting.

title: microwaved pizza franks
directions: Place franks in buns.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Top each frank with 2 tablespoons of sauce.
Place prepared buns in 18 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle each with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave 3 minutes on High or until cheese melts.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix as Butter Cake.

title: snow cream
directions: Long ago when winter was long and cold my Great-Granddad made Snow Cream.
Mix milk, sugar and vanilla until desired sweetness. Add fluffy white snow.
Stir quickly until blended and thick.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with fork and spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
For filling, combine pumpkin, eggs, sugars, cinnamon and milk.
Mix well and spread over first layer.
Third layer is dry cake mix, stick of oleo, 1/4 cup sugar and nuts.
Mix and crumble on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: easy beefy bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In a 2 1/2-quart ovenproof skillet or flameproof casserole, cook bacon, beef and onion over medium-high heat on top of the stove, stirring occasionally, until bacon is crisp and beef is browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in barbecue sauce, mustard and Worcestershire sauce until well blended.
Add baked beans, pinto beans and mustard greens, Swiss chard or spinach.
Stir gently to mix.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes, or until very hot in center and bubbly.
Remove from oven and serve.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt
butter in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Tear bread in small pieces and sprinkle over butter.
Sprinkle sausage over bread. Then
sprinkle cheese.
Beat eggs and add other ingredients;
pour over
cheese.
Chill
for 8 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with cream, ending with flour.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turkey florentine
directions: Roast turkey according to package directions.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Stir in spinach and ham.
Place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake alongside turkey last 45 minutes of roasting time.
Slice turkey and serve with Florentine rice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: snowball cake
directions: Remove all the brown from the angel food cake and pinch into bite-sized pieces.
Set aside.
Dissolve gelatine in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water, pineapple juice, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until mixture is partly congealed. Whip two packages of Dream Whip according to package directions. Fold into gelatine mixture.

title: hidden peach fruit salad
directions: Combine the cherries, oranges and grapes.
Add the fruit cocktail.
Mix with peach pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add the bananas.
Put in your favorite pedestal or clear glass bowl.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Add consomme, onion soup and seasoning from wild rice package.
Add rice and mushrooms.
Stir.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: yummy chicken dinner
directions: In roasting pan, heat oil and butter.
Add flour and stir until light brown.
Add cup of liquid slowly, stirring to make gravy.
Meanwhile, have potatoes, carrots and onion sliced rather thin.
Mix with salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and the condensed onion soup.
Put potato mixture in gravy and place cut up chicken on top.
Cook about 1 hour at 350°.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: cognac-braised quail
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (180° C).
Heat butter in large ovenproof casserole or skillet over medium heat.
Add quail and sear birds about 6 to 8 minutes, browning on all sides.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook another 2 minutes.
Pour in cognac and flambe or cook 2 minutes over high heat to evaporate alcohol.
Add wine and bring to boil.
Add all seasonings.
Stir in gravy.
Cover and cook 30 minutes in oven.
Serves 4.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients.
Add salt, pepper, ground beef and tomato sauce.
Brown.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until well done at 350°.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine meal, milk and beaten eggs; mix well.
Add boiling water.
Pour into baking dish and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 450°.

title: buttery lemon squares
directions: Beat butter with 1/2 cup powdered sugar until creamy.
Add 2 cups flour; beat until blended.
Spread evenly in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar; beat until thick and well blended.
Add juice, 1/3 cup flour and baking powder.
Beat until blended.
Pour over crust and return to oven.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: farmer's pork chops
directions: Brown chops and garlic in hot oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place potatoes in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan. Top with browned chops.
Separate onion slices into rings and lay over chops.
Blend sour cream, salt and mustard and pour over potatoes, chops and onions.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fast bubbles
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Combine softened cream cheese, soup and milk.
Add salt, catsup, olives and ground beef. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Place biscuits around edge of casserole dish (if desired top with sliced olives).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, Worcestershire, bread, egg and salt and pepper to taste.
Make small balls, about 75, and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown.
Drain.
Mix barbecue sauce and preserves on top of stove.
Add meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Warm soup (do not put in water).
Mix water and gelatine and add to warm soup.
Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Add onion, celery and crab meat and mix together.
Pour into a mold and let set.
Serve with crackers.
Mold should be buttered or sprayed with nonstick pan coating.

title: green rice
directions: Heat oil, rice and salt in skillet that can be covered tightly.
Mix vegetables and add to skillet with water and food coloring.
Cover and simmer until done, approximately 1/2 hour. Do not uncover while simmering.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Heat oven before you start to mix.
All ingredients must be room temperature.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Cut pork into bite-size pieces and layer in casserole dish 1/2 of pork, then 1/2 of pepper strips, then 1/2 of onion rings.
Dot with 1/2 of catsup.
Repeat, using remaining half.
Salt to taste. Pour pork broth over this, barely covering meat, etc.
Bake at 400° for about 1/2 hour uncovered.
Keep mashing down onion tips and pepper tips so they won't burn.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk, salt and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Drop on foil.
